2008-01-31  Martin Leidig  <mleidig@schlund.de>

	Released Pfixcore 0.12.0

	* build.xml: Change version number

2008-01-21  Sebastian Marsching  <sebastian.marsching@1und1.de>

	* startTomcat.sh: 
	Removed "jni/lib" from LD_LIBRARY_PATH (was only used by AppLoader)

2008-01-18  Sebastian Marsching  <sebastian.marsching@1und1.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/editor2/frontend/resources/SessionResourceImpl.java: 
	* projects/core/editor2/conf/edit.conf.xml: 
	* projects/core/editor2/txt/pages/main_login.xml: 
	Switched editor servlet to role-based authentication mechanism.

2008-01-18  Martin Leidig  <mleidig@schlund.de>

	Renamed SimpleTypeSerializer and ComplexTypeSerializer annotations
	to SimpleTypeSerializerClass and ComplexTypeSeriailizerClass to 
	avoid name clashes/irritations with the serializer interface names.

	Modified:
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/oxm/impl/serializers/BeanSerializer.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/oxm/impl/annotation/DateSerializer.java

	Removed:
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/oxm/impl/annotation/ComplexTypeSerializer.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/oxm/impl/annotation/SimpleTypeSerializer.java

	Added:
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/oxm/impl/annotation/ComplexTypeSerializerClass.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/oxm/impl/annotation/SimpleTypeSerializerClass.java

2008-01-18  Martin Leidig  <mleidig@schlund.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/context/RequestContextImpl.java: reset
	HashSet for circular authpage reference detection in handleRequestWorker 

2008-01-16  Martin Leidig  <mleidig@schlund.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/context/RequestContextImpl.java:
	Added dynamic check for circular authpage references, prohibit context
	authpage to be used as authconstraint authpage
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/config/impl/ConditionRule.java: throw
	exception if 'hasrole' references non-existing role
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/config/impl/ContextConfigImpl.java: Disable
	loadtime check of authconstraints by default (new runtime checks
	suffice)

2008-01-14  Martin Leidig  <mleidig@schlund.de>

	Removed the authentication flag. The Authentication object is
	considered as being always authenticated (found no use case for
	need of explicit control).

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/auth/Authentication.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/context/RequestContextImpl.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/ContextImpl.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/example/bank/ihandler/LoginHandler.java

	* projects/core/schema/properties200401.xsd: Added default attribute
	definition for authconstraint elements.

	* de/schlund/pfixxml/config/impl/ContextConfigImpl.java: Added check
	for circular authpage references and context authpage after reading
	in configuration (now authpages aren't allowed to have authconstraints
	which have the page itself as direct or indirect authpage, also a
	Context's authpage isn't allowed to be used as authconstraint authpage.

2008-01-14  Martin Leidig  <mleidig@schlund.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/ResultDocument.java: addObject(Element element, 
	String name, Object object) now returns the newly-created element instead 
	of the passed element.

2008-01-07  Martin Leidig  <mleidig@schlund.de>

	Improved file change detection of apt task by saving timestamp file of
	last apt run.
	Added automatic Caster configuration for builtin types.

	Modified:
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/generator/iwrpgen/IWrapperFileScanner.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/generator/iwrpgen/IWrapperAnnotationProcessor.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/generator/iwrpgen/AptTask.java

2008-01-07  Martin Leidig  <mleidig@schlund.de>

	Changed serialization format: use derived classname as element 
	name for Map/Array/Collection entries.
	Added classname mapping customization support via @ClassNameAlias 
	annotation.
	Added XPath reference generation support to XMLWriter and 
	SerializationContext, which allows circular dependencies to be 
	serialized as xpathref attributes containing XPath expressions 
	referencing the according element.
	Added support for custom ComplexTypeSerializer implementations.

	Modified:
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/oxm/impl/SerializerRegistry.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/oxm/impl/serializers/BeanSerializer.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/oxm/impl/serializers/CollectionSerializer.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/oxm/impl/serializers/MapSerializer.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/oxm/impl/serializers/ArraySerializer.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/oxm/impl/serializers/ObjectToStringSerializer.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/oxm/impl/DOMWriter.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/oxm/impl/SerializationContext.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/oxm/impl/XMLWriter.java

	Added:
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/oxm/impl/DOMXPathPosition.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/oxm/impl/XPathPosition.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/oxm/impl/ClassNameMapping.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/oxm/impl/annotation/ClassNameAlias.java


2008-01-03  Martin Leidig  <mleidig@schlund.de>

	Added support for custom serializers to the Object-XML-Mapping framework.
	Own serializer implementations can be written implementing the
	SimpleTypeSerializer interface. The serializers can be set at bean
	members/getters using custom annotations (marked themselves by the
	SimpleTypeSerializer annotation).
	Added a DateSerializer implementation, which supports customization
	of the date format via annotations, e.g.: @DateSerializer("yyyy-MM-dd")
	The samplebank application now uses the ResultDocument.addObject()-method 
	for building the result tree (instead of manually building the DOM).

	Added:
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/oxm/impl/annotation
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/oxm/impl/annotation/ComplexTypeSerializer.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/oxm/impl/annotation/SimpleTypeSerializer.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/oxm/impl/annotation/DateSerializer.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/oxm/impl/AnnotationAware.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/oxm/impl/serializers/DateSerializer.java

	Modified:
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/oxm/impl/SerializerRegistry.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/oxm/impl/serializers/BeanSerializer.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/example/bank/model/BankInMemoryDAO.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/example/bank/model/Account.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/example/bank/context/ContextAccountImpl.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/example/bank/context/ContextCustomerImpl.java
	* projects/samplebank/txt/pages/main_accountoverview.xml

2007-12-12  jtl  <jtl@schlund.de>

	* projects/core/build/iwrapper.xsl: conditionalize annotion import

2007-12-11  jtl  <jtl@schlund.de>

	* projects/core/schema/properies200401.xsd:
	* projects/core/xsl/master.xsl:
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/util/TransformerCallback.java: 
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/context/RequestContextImpl.java: 
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/SPDocument.java: 
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/config/PageRequestConfig.java: 
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/config/impl/PageRequestConfigImpl.java: 
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/config/impl/PagerequestRule.java: 
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/config/impl/PagerequestVariantRule.java: remove 
	nostore/storeXML/setNostore stuff. This is no longer needed. We normally don't store 
	a document, only if it's a redirect or the XSLT trafo explicitly requests it (e.g. for frames). 
	This also means, that the session cleaner normally doesn't have to do anything, only if the 
	next request from a redirect or a frame is somehow lost.
	 
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/util/CacheValueLRU.java: new file. Implement a LRU Cache 
	on the number of distinct VALUES, not keys. 
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/SessionCleaner.java: use it there instead of the old map
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/AbstractXMLServlet.java: also here, and remove the nostore handling, too
	when we are already here :-) Now you actively have to use the callback from the xslt file to
	force a storing of the document or the document is a redirect. Normally we won't store anything anymore.
	 
	projects/sample1/conf/depend.xml
	projects/sample1/conf/config.conf.xml
	projects/sample1/xml/manyframes.xml: added "frames" page for testing frame related stuff
	
	
2007-12-09  Martin Leidig  <mleidig@schlund.de>

	Extended role based authorization. New features are:
	- Declarative authconstraints, which can be assigned
	to pagerequests; authconstraints define authorization
	conditions, supported are: 'hasrole', 'and', 'or' and
	'not', represented by according XML elements. Using 
	the 'authpage' attribute you can define the page, which
	should be called on authorization failure. Using the
	'default' attribute you can set one toplevel authconstraint
	to be the default one for all pagerequest having no
	authconstraint asssigned
	- Pagerequests can either define new authconstraints
	as child elements or can reference existing toplevel
	authconstraints
	- Roles can be automatically set on context initialization
	using the 'initial' attribute
	- The Authentication object is automatically set on
	startup (it hasn't to be created manually any more), roles
	can be added using 'addRole()' and removed using 'revokeRole()'
	- You can check the current roles from XSLT using the
	'pfx:hasRole' extension function

	Added:
	* projects/samplebank/txt/pages/main_home.xml
	* projects/samplebank/txt/pages/main_test.xml
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/auth/AuthConstraintImpl.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/auth/AuthConstraint.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/auth/AuthConstraintViolation.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/auth/Condition.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/auth/conditions
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/auth/conditions/And.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/auth/conditions/ConditionGroup.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/auth/conditions/HasRole.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/auth/conditions/Not.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/auth/conditions/Or.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/auth/RoleProvider.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/config/impl/AuthConstraintRule.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/config/impl/ConditionRule.java

	Removed:
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/auth/AccessDeniedException.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/config/impl/PageAccessConfigImpl.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/config/impl/PageAccessRule.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/config/impl/RoleConfigImpl.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/config/PageAccessConfig.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/config/RoleConfig.java

	Modified:
