2007-12-01 Jens Lautenbacher <jtl@schlund.de>
	Cosmetic stuff part II - removed some more warnings...

2007-11-30 Jens Lautenbacher <jtl@schlund.de>
	Cosmetic stuff part I - removed some warnings...

2007-11-19  Sebastian Marsching <sebastian.marsching@1und1.de>

	* docs/:
	Added support for Docbook based documentation.

2007-11-09  Martin Leidig  <mleidig@schlund.de>

	Added dependency entries for all required (mandatory) libraries to
	pom.xml. As public maven repositories don't contain all this libraries
	and some of them come with an out-dated pom.xml, transitive dependency
	resolution may not work or will need some manual adjustments and
	conflict resolutions. 
	By the way we should look if we can update some out-dated libraries
	and replace some old libraries, for which new replacements are
	available (e.g. replace jakarta-oro library usage with java.util.regex).

	* pom.xml: Added mandatory library dependencies
	* build-maven.xml: Added test target, which retrieves all dependent
	libraries

2007-11-07  Martin Leidig  <mleidig@schlund.de>

	Automatically insert token parameter in forms when requiresToken is set
	in the configuration.

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/util/TransformerCallback.java: added requiresToken()
	method, which checks if form submit to a page need token parameter
	* projects/core/xsl/forminput.xsl: automatically insert token form parameter
	if form contains no pfx:token element but needs a token (detected via Java callback) 
	* projects/core/xsl/functions.xsl: added pfx:requiresToken function, which
	does Java callback to check if the passed page needs a form token
	* projects/sample1/conf/config.conf.xml: set requirestoken at order
	input element
	* projects/sample1/txt/pages/main_order.xml: remove pfx:token from
	form

2007-11-06  Martin Leidig  <mleidig@schlund.de>

	Upgraded to Spring version 2.0.7
	* lib/spring-1.2.1.jar: Removed
	* lib/spring-2.0.7.jar: Added

2007-11-06  Martin Leidig  <mleidig@schlund.de>

	Added support for manual IWrapper instantiation and population. Using the new
	IWrapper method loadFromStringValues() you can load the IWrapper's typed data 
	from the String representations set via the setStringValXXX methods, i.e. the 
	string values are processed (checked and casted) just like values provided by 
	a RequestData object (includes the setting of statuscodes). Amongst others it 
	can be used to manually instantiate and populate IWrapper objects within unit 
	tests.

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/generator/IWrapper.java: added loadFromStringValues()
	method to interface
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/generator/IWrapperImpl.java: loadFromStringValues()
	implementation calling initFromStringValue() for all parameters
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/generator/IWrapperParam.java: extract parameter
	checking and casting from initValueFromRequest() method into new method
	checkValue(). Added new method initFromStringValue() which uses the string
	representation as parameter and calls checkValue().
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/generator/IWrapperIndexedParam.java: added method
	initFromStringValue(), which calls initFromStringValue() for all containing
	parameters.

2007-10-30  Martin Leidig  <mleidig@schlund.de>

	Added new file upload parameter type, which provides more information than the 
	raw java.io.File. Using the new type de.schlund.pfixxml.multipart.UploadFile you
	also get information about files which exceeded the part size limit. The mime
	type is available too. 

	Added:

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/generator/IWrapperParam.java: Removed tmp file existence
	check, because now FileData without backing local file is allowed	
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/multipart/UploadFile.java: New interface for
	uploaded files
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/generator/casters/ToUploadFile.java: casts FileData param
	values to UploadFile objects
	* projects/sample1/txt/pages/main_upload.xml: Added test page with
	single und multiple file upload tests.
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/example/iwrapper/FileUpload.iwrp: single file upload
	wrapper
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/example/iwrapper/MultiFileUpload.iwrp: multiple file
	upload wrapper
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/example/ContextFileUpload.java: show upload status
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/example/FileUploadHandler.java: handle single file upload
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/example/ContextFileUploadImpl.java: show upload status
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/example/MultiFileUploadHandler.java: handle multiple file
	upload

	Modified:

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/multipart/MultipartHandler.java: don't create FileData
	for empty upload parts, but create FileData for upload parts exceeding the maximum
	file size; warning cleanup
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/multipart/FileData.java: Added implementation
	of UploadFile interface methods
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/multipart/HeaderStruct.java: warning cleanup
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/multipart/MultipartStream.java: warning cleanup
	* projects/core/dyntxt/statusmessages.xml: Added statuscode for UploadFile
	* projects/sample1/conf/config.conf.xml: Added pagerequest and context
	resource for file upload page.
	* projects/sample1/conf/depend.xml: Added file upload page.

