2007-10-26  Martin Leidig  <mleidig@schlund.de>

	Added table showing all configured IWrappers and their parameters for the
	current page in the editor-mode-XML-only DOM-tree view.

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/util/TransformerCallback.java: added new method
	which returns a nodelist containing all configured IWrappers and their
	prefixes
	* projects/core/xsl/xmlfontify.xsl: added XSLT which retrieves the IWrapper
	list for the current page, iterates over the IWrappers, gets the IWrapper
	information and shows the data in a table

2007-10-26  Martin Leidig  <mleidig@schlund.de>
	
	Added support for forcing form submit tokens. It's enabled by setting
	the 'requirestoken'-attribute at the according pagerequest/input element	
	to 'true'. 
			
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/app/DefaultIWrapperState.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/config/PageRequestConfig.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/config/impl/PageRequestConfigImpl.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/config/impl/PagerequestInputRule.java
	* projects/core/schema/properties200401.xsd
	* projects/core/dyntxt/statusmessages.xml

2007-10-26  Martin Leidig  <mleidig@schlund.de>

	* build-maven.xml: Add skel archive as artifact attachment.	
	* pom.xml: Set version to 0.11.2

2007-10-25  Martin Leidig  <mleidig@schlund.de>

	* build.xml: Don't include saxon8.x jars into skeleton archive.

2007-10-25  Martin Leidig  <mleidig@schlund.de>

	Improved error page of UniversalExceptionProcessor. Now all exception causes are
	shown (needed cause the toplevel exceptions aren't meaningful enough). All stacktraces
	are available too (and additionally are collapsible).

	* projects/core/xsl/errorrepresentation.xsl: show exception causes too, made 
	stacktrace view collapsible via Javascript, force wrapping of long strings in XSLT
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/exceptionprocessor/util/XMLCreatorVisitor.java: recursively
	append exception causes (with stacktraces) to DOM tree

2007-10-23  Martin Leidig  <mleidig@schlund.de>

	Added role-based authorization support. Now it's possible to define roles
	and assign authorizations to them. Currently we only support pageaccess
	authorizations, further authorizations, like method access will be possible
	in later releases.
	Roles can be assigned to the current user or session by setting an Authentication
	object using the Context's setAuthentication method. The pageaccess authorization 
	is done by interfering documentFromCurrentStep() and checking if the current
	roles permit accessing the current page. The role definition and assignment of
	authorizations is done in the ContextXMLServlet's configuration file.

	Added:

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/auth
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/auth/Authentication.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/auth/AuthorizationException.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/auth/AuthorizationInterceptor.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/auth/AuthenticationImpl.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/auth/Role.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/auth/NotAuthenticatedException.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/auth/RoleImpl.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/auth/AccessDeniedException.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/auth/RoleNotFoundException.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/auth/AuthenticationException.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/config/impl/PageAccessConfigImpl.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/config/impl/PageAccessRule.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/config/impl/RoleConfigImpl.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/config/impl/RoleRule.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/config/PageAccessConfig.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/config/RoleConfig.java

