	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/perflogging/IntervalFactory.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/perflogging/PerfEvent.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/AbstractXMLServlet.java

	Added SessionAdminMbean and refactored
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/serverutil/SessionAdminMBean.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/serverutil/SessionAdmin.java

	Moved servlet from jmx package:
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/JmxPortServlet.java

	Removed JMX server configuration and added TestRecording factory:
	* projects/common/conf/factory.xml

	Refactored:
	* tests/junit/de/schlund/pfixxml/jmx/ApplicationListTest.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/AbstractXMLServlet.java
	
2007-10-04  Martin Leidig  <mleidig@schlund.de>

	Trace transformations failing with UnsupportedOperationExceptions (Saxon's
	intensional nodeset dependency bug). Thus we try to find out what and where
	it happens exactly. The tracing is done by catching the exception and 
	repeating the transformation once again with a registered tracelistener, 
	which is logging out the trace steps.

	Added: 
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/util/xsltimpl/Saxon1TraceListener.java

	Modified:
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/util/Xslt.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/util/XsltSupport.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/util/xsltimpl/XsltSaxon1.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/util/xsltimpl/XsltSaxon2.java

2007-09-28  Sebastian Marsching  <sebastian.marsching@1und1.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/SessionContextStore.java: 
	Delegate HttpSessionBindingEvents to context instances.
	
	* projects/core/editor2/conf/scriptedflows/selectinclude.xsl: 
	* projects/core/editor2/conf/edit.conf.xml: 
	* projects/core/xsl/include.xsl: 
	* projects/core/xsl/include_xslt2.xsl: 
	Replaced auxhandler for include part selection with scripted flow in
	preparation for the removal of auxhandler support.
	
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/ContextXMLServlet.java: 
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/context/RequestContextImpl.java: 
	Moved the URL redirection code from context to servlet in order to make it work
	with scripted flows. However, SSL redirect handling is still managed in the 
	context. 	
	
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/ContextImpl.java: 
	Implemented HttpSessionBindingListener to change session object stored in
	SessionContextImpl when context is bound to another session (e.g. on SSL switch)

2007-09-19  Martin Leidig  <mleidig@schlund.de>

	* skel/build-skel.xml: change junit task error behaviour: now halt
	on failures and errors instead of errors only.

2007-09-19  Martin Leidig  <mleidig@schlund.de>

	* projects/core/script/webservice.js: allow Null values for
	bean properties
	* projects/webservice/htdocs/typetest-pfxsoap.js: add new
	tests for Null values

2007-09-18  Martin Leidig  <mleidig@schlund.de>

	* projects/core/script/webservice.js: support Null values for 
	Date and Calendar objects (bugfix)

2007-09-12  Martin Leidig  <mleidig@schlund.de>

	Improved extension function exception handling: Due to an 
	unfortunate implementation of Saxon's FunctionProxy only 
	the exception message and no stacktrace or cause of an error, 
	occurred within an extension function, is available in the 
	resulting TransformerException. Using the ExtensionFunctionUtils
	class an extension function can catch its exceptions and store 
	it threadlocally calling the method setExtensionFunctionError. 
	Later, during exception handling, the  exception can be retrieved 
	calling getExtensionFunctionError(). This mechanism is used by
	TransformerCallback and Xslt to subsequently add the extension 
	function exception to the TransformerException.

	* de/schlund/pfixxml/util/ExtensionFunctionUtils.java
	* de/schlund/pfixcore/util/TransformerCallback.java
	* de/schlund/pfixxml/util/Xslt.java

2007-09-10  Martin Leidig  <mleidig@schlund.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/SessionContextStore.java: added method
	getServletNames() which returns the servlet names under which
	Contexts are stored (needed for generic access to Context by
	various applications)

2007-09-06  Sebastian Marsching  <sebastian.marsching@1und1.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/AbstractXMLServlet.java: 
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/SessionCleaner.java: 
	* projects/core/xsl/master.xsl: 
	Register frames for SPDocument reuse and delete the SPDocument after
	all frames have been rendered.

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/context/RequestContextImpl.java: 
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/ContextImpl.java: 
	Fixed an exception occurring when the Context#isAuthorized() method was 
	called and the context had not been authenticated yet.
	

2007-09-06  Martin Leidig  <mleidig@schlund.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/ContextXMLServlet.java: synchronize the first 
	call of tryReloadProperties because a race condition can lead to a 
	NullPointerException with servercontext being null.

2007-08-22  Martin Leidig  <mleidig@schlund.de>

	Send webservice authentication error responses in the requested webservice
	protocol instead of simple 500 errors with a text message. Therefore every
	ServiceProcessor has to implement the new method processException. This
	method should write a response containing the passed Exception in the
	according webservice protocol. Besides authentication errors now throw
	a typed Exception, AuthenticationException, which derives the formerly
	used ServiceException.

	Added:
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/AuthenticationException.java

	Modified:
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/ServiceProcessor.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/ServiceRuntime.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/jsonqx/JSONQXProcessor.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/jsonws/JSONWSProcessor.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/WebServiceServlet.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/ServiceException.java
	* projects/core/script/xmlRequest.js

2007-08-17  Martin Leidig  <mleidig@schlund.de>

	* projects/core/script/webservice.js: Fixed bug: extracted wrong session id 
	from URLs containing anchors and no parameters.

2007-08-15  Martin Leidig  <mleidig@schlund.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/generator/iwrpgen/AptTask.java: increase maximum
	memory for apt to 512MB

2007-08-10  Martin Leidig  <mleidig@schlund.de>

	* skel/build-skel.xml: Moved the webservice ant task definition into its
	own target and made the webservice target depending on it. Thus the webservice
	task is loaded by its own classloader and not the one that is used by the other 
	tasks. This ensures that at instantiation time all necessary libraries are
	available to the classloader, even libraries which only become available later
	during the build process, after the common ant task loader has already been
	instantiated to load the other ant tasks.

2007-08-07  Martin Leidig  <mleidig@schlund.de>

	Added missing IWrapper runtime information for auth- and aux-wrappers.

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/generator/IWrapperInfo.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/app/DefaultAuthIWrapperState.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/util/TransformerCallback.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/config/PageRequestConfig.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/config/IWrapperConfig.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/config/impl/PageRequestConfigImpl.java

2007-08-03  termi  <termi@prometheus.local.marsching.com>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/resources/ResourceUtil.java: 
	Replace spaces in URIs with %20s.

2007-08-02  jtl  <jtl@schlund.de>

	* projects/core/xsl/forminput.xsl: Added <pfx:externalform href="..."> template to route an external form
	over the deref server.
	Changed checking of IWrapper and their parameters to use the new runtime checking via callbacks (see below).
	This will now also work for parameter names that are constructed at runtime (e.g. indexed parameters)
	* projects/core/xsl/master.xsl: added __formwarn template for runtime checking of the validity of 
	IWrappers and their parameters.
	Also add __sign template to go along the __enc template: __deref will now call both of them.	
	* projects/sample1/txt/pages/main_home.xml: Make a test case for the new form-over-dereferer servlet stuff
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/DerefServlet.java (handleLink): added the possibility to add all "remaining" submitted 
	parameters to the link that is stripped from the referer. Needed to enable to route form submits (where no final 
	link parameter with the host + all the parameters can be constructed) over the deref servlet. In this case the signing will 
	only guard the hostname.
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/generator/IWrapperInfo.java: "martin style" -> "other people esp. jtl" style
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/util/TransformerCallback.java: don't throw an Exception if a wrapper is not found, 
	just return null
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/app/IWrapperSimpleContainer.java: removed insertion of extended status 

