	Minor changes in javascript code for edit console

2007-05-30  jtl  <jtl@schlund.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/util/DumpText.java: small cleanups 

2007-05-29  Martin Leidig  <mleidig@schlund.de>

	* projects/core/build/create_apacheconf.xsl: Removed the FollowSymLinks 
	option from the Location section, because it's ignored by Apache. Removed 
	the AllowOverride directive too, because it's only valid inside Directory 
	sections. Perhaps we should remove the entire section, but using Options
	without + or -, they aren't merged with other default options and some
	environments might have less restrictive defaults and could rely on  
	disabling some options (and enabling CGI execution via ExecCGI).

2007-05-29  Martin Leidig  <mleidig@schlund.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/ServletManager.java: Improved ExceptionProcessor
	retrieval. Now we retrieve the configured ExceptionProcessor by walking
	up the throwable's type hierarchy via reflection.

2007-05-25  jtl  <jtl@schlund.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/util/DumpText.java: 
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/util/ImportText.java: new tools to dump and 
	import used include parts 
	* projects/dumptext.sh:
	* projects/importtext.sh: use the tools above.

2007-05-23  Martin Leidig  <mleidig@schlund.de>

	Added form submit token mechanism which can be used to prevent
	duplicate form submissions and handle transactional processing
	requirements.
	Using the pfx:token tag a hidden field with a random token is
	included into the parent form. The token is stored in the Context,
	keyed by a customizable name (by default pagename#elementid,
	which can be overwritten/replaced using the @name attribute).
	After the form is submitted the token is invalidated, submitting
	the form again causes the setting of a page message. Via the
	@errorpage attribute you can optionally jump to an error page. 

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/app/DefaultIWrapperState.java:
	Check if token was submitted and if it is valid, if not set
	page message or error page
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/ContextImpl.java: Implement
	TokenManager interface, hold Map with tokens
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/util/TokenUtils.java: New helper class
	providing token generation
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/util/TokenManager.java: Token management
	interface providing methods to create, validate and reset tokens
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/util/TransformerCallback.java: Added
	callback to create token
	* projects/sample1/txt/pages/main_tokenerror.xml: sample error 
	page called when form is double submitted 
	* projects/sample1/txt/pages/main_home.xml: added pfx:token tag
	to form (with errorpage attribute)
	* projects/sample1/txt/pages/main_order.xml: added pfx:token tag
	to form (without errorpage)
	* projects/sample1/conf/config.conf.xml: added error page
	* projects/sample1/conf/depend.xml: added error page
	* projects/core/xsl/forminput.xsl: added template handling the
	pfx:token tag (inserting token as hidden field)
	* projects/core/xsl/functions.xsl: added callback function for
	token creation
	* projects/core/dyntxt/statusmessages.xml: added statuscode for
	token validation error

2007-05-18  Sebastian Marsching  <sebastian.marsching@1und1.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/AbstractContextServletFilter.java: 
	* projects/core/conf/web.xml: 
	* projects/core/xsl/create_webxml.xsl: 
	Adding support for servlet filters.

2007-05-15  Martin Leidig  <mleidig@schlund.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/ServletManager.java: Implemented new
	ExceptionConfig management. The old behaviour was strange and
	buggy: ExceptionConfig objects were retrieved by accident,
	because they were hold in a Map and were retrieved by iterating
	over the Map's keys and doing an instanceof test. Therefore it
	could happen that different ExceptionConfig objects were
	returned for the same Exception class. Now retrieving is done
	by first trying to get the ExceptionConfig object by key, if
	none is found an iteration with instanceof testing is done.
	The iteration order is still undefined, because the underlying
	properties are not ordered.

2007-05-15  Martin Leidig  <mleidig@schlund.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/ServiceRuntime.java: throw
	Exception if session context can't be retrieved

2007-05-14  Martin Leidig  <mleidig@schlund.de>

	Fixed race condition in iframe fallback handling.
	Changed fallback HTML element names to allow simultaneous
	usage of both request implementations:

	* projects/core/script/httpRequest.js
	* projects/core/script/xmlRequest.js

	Added service request dumping support (especially for 
	improved, more verbose, exception reporting).

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/ServiceRuntime.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/ServiceRequest.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/jsonws/JSONWSProcessor.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/HttpServiceRequest.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/ServiceRequestWrapper.java

2007-05-14  Sebastian Marsching  <sebastian.marsching@1und1.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/DerefServlet.java (handleLink): 
	Added code that does a javascript redirect in case the HTTP refresh
	redirect does not work (ugly IE7-workaround).

2007-05-11  Martin Leidig  <mleidig@schlund.de>

	Enable native XMLHttpRequest usage by default for Opera (instead
	of iframe fallback), because current versions don't have problems
	any longer.

	* projects/core/script/httpRequest.js
	* projects/core/script/xmlRequest.js

2007-05-10  Martin Leidig  <mleidig@schlund.de>

	Released Pfixcore 0.10.1
	
	* build.xml: Changed development version to 0.10.2-pre

2007-05-09  Martin Leidig  <mleidig@schlund.de>

	Fixed "Cookie setting problem with reused SPDocuments". Cookies still
	aren't set at responses based on a reused DOM, but now they're set at
	error responses (including 302 status responses) too.

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/AbstractXMLServlet.java: Set cookies on error
	responses.

2007-05-08  Martin Leidig  <mleidig@schlund.de>

	Fixed "multiple getWriter() call problem", which could occur when an 
	exception is thrown during the writing of a JSON response, which in
	turn can trigger a ServletException and a second getWriter() call.

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/WebServiceServlet.java: Don't throw
	ServletException if HttpServletResponse is already committed.
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/jsonws/JSONWSProcessor.java: Ensure
	that Writers are closed before returning to the caller.

