2007-02-28  Sebastian Marsching  <sebastian.marsching@1und1.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/scriptedflow/vm/ScriptVM.java (mangleDoc): 
	Fixed bug in iteration over NodeList: Indexes in NodeList are not constant
	if one of the nodes is deleted.
	
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/DocrootServlet.java: 
	* projects/core/build/create_serverxml.xsl: 
	* projects/core/build/create_webxml.xsl: 
	In standalone mode server passthrough resources using the DocrootServlet
	instead of creating special context instances in Tomcat configuration.

2007-02-26  Martin Leidig  <mleidig@schlund.de>

	* skel/build-skel.xml: Added new target "check-buildskel", which
	checks if a build-skel.xml in the Pustefix root directory exists
	if it's older than the version from the pfixcore distribution and
	if its content changed. On these conditions the build is stopped
	and the user is requested to replace the old version.

2007-02-23  Martin Leidig  <mleidig@schlund.de>

	Fixed corrupted 304 response problem. 304 Responses for cached
	documents (the new ETag support) must not set a content-type that
	is handled by mod_deflate, because old mod_deflate versions have a bug 
	and gzip the 304 responses too, which causes non-empty response bodies,
	which in turn confuses browsers and leads to long loading times
	and broken documents (especially in conjunction with mod_ssl).

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/AbstractXMLServlet.java: Reset content type
	for 304 responses.

2007-02-23  Sebastian Marsching  <sebastian.marsching@1und1.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/config/impl/ContextXMLServletConfigImpl.java: 
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/config/impl/ServletInfoRule.java: 
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/exceptionprocessor/UniversalExceptionProcessor.java: 
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/targets/TargetGenerator.java: 
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/AbstractXMLServlet.java: 
	* projects/core/build/create_webxml.xsl: 
	Made path to depend.xml available using a init-parameter. TargetGenerator can
	now lookup its name in projects.xml, if it is not specified in depend.xml.
	Removed deprecated xmlserver.depend.xml property from servlet configuration.
	XSD for servlet configuration has not been changed yet for compatibility
	reasons, so the depend attribute is still required by the schema. 

2007-02-22  Martin Leidig  <mleidig@schlund.de>

	Renamed JSON bean (de-)serialization annotations. As 'Transient'
	fits better in durability or persistence contexts, I decided to
	just call them @ExcludeByDefault, @Include and @Exclude, stating
	that they mark the properties to be included/excluded in a
	context independent way.

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/beans/Include.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/beans/BeanDescriptor.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/beans/Property.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/beans/Transient.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/beans/TransientByDefault.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/beans/Exclude.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/beans/ExcludeByDefault.java
	* tests/junit/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/beans/BeanA.java
	* tests/junit/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/beans/BeanB.java
	* tests/junit/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/beans/BeanC.java
	* tests/junit/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/beans/BeanD.java
	* tests/junit/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/beans/BeanE.java
	* tests/junit/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/beans/BeanF.java

2007-02-20  Martin Leidig  <mleidig@schlund.de>

	Added support for Bean serialization/deserialization customization
	via Java annotations to the JSON webservice framework. The annotation
	@Transient can be used at getter methods to exclude the according 
	property from serialization/deserialization, @TransientByDefault at
	classes makes all properties declared by that class transient by 
	default, using @Property at the getters includes the according 
	property again.

	Refactored and improved exception handling:
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/jsonws/SerializerRegistry.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/jsonws/DeserializerRegistry.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/jsonws/serializers/BeanSerializer.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/jsonws/JSONWSProcessor.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/jsonws/deserializers/BeanDeserializer.java	

	Added new package for bean introspection stuff:
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/beans

	Moved exisiting bean introspection classes to new package and added
	annotation support:
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/beans/BeanDescriptor.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/beans/BeanDescriptorFactory.java

	Added bean(-property) annotations:
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/beans/Property.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/beans/Transient.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/beans/TransientByDefault.java

	Added unit test for bean property introspection:
	* tests/junit/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/beans/BeanDescriptorTest.java
	* tests/junit/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/beans/BeanA.java
	* tests/junit/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/beans/BeanB.java
	* tests/junit/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/beans/BeanC.java
	* tests/junit/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/beans/BeanD.java
	* tests/junit/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/beans/BeanE.java
	* tests/junit/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/beans/BeanF.java


2007-02-20  Martin Leidig  <mleidig@schlund.de>

	* skel/build-skel.xml: Fixed task classpath problem with missing build dir: 
	after realclean tasks can't find classes in the build directory despite they 
	are existing (were created in the meantime resp.), but at the time the task
	is initialized the build dir doesn't exist and when the task is called it's
	omitted. Solution: dependence on the init target didn't work because of 
	circular references, so I made an additional target init-dirs, on which the
	init and ant-tasks target depend.

2007-02-20  Sebastian Marsching  <sebastian.marsching@1und1.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/context/RequestContextImpl.java: 
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/ServiceRuntime.java: 
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/AbstractXMLServlet.java: 
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/ContextXMLServlet.java: 
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/DirectOutputServlet.java: 
	Changed handling for SSL switching: Redirect is always sent when 
	SSL switching is needed regardless of the nostore flag. 
	AbstractXMLServer stores the document on a redirect, even if the 
	nostore flag is set.
	Context instance is now registered using the hashcode of the servlet
	and the URI handler associated with the servlet. Thus a foreign context
	can be reffered to using the handler URI instead of a synthetic name.

2007-02-19  Martin Leidig  <mleidig@schlund.de>

	Improved caching of bean descriptors, now they're cached 
	JSONWSProcessor-wide.

