2007-02-13  Martin Leidig  <mleidig@schlund.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/AbstractXMLServlet.java: don't reuse SPDocument
	if it has a pagename that differs from the one in the request

2007-02-12  Martin Leidig  <mleidig@schlund.de>

	Added support for deployment of external webapps. Support can be
	enabled by adding <webapps hostbased="true"/> to project.xml.in.
	With this option the project/host gets its own webapps directory
	servletconf/webapps_PROJECTNAME. At the moment the Pustefix webapps
	are still deployed to the shared webapps directory, but external
	webapps can be deployed to the host specific webapps directory and
	thus can have their own context descriptor in META-INF. Additional
	webapps are automatically deployed, if they are placed inside the
	directory servletconf/autodeploy/webapps_PROJECTNAME. Project
	specific JkMount directives can be added to project.xml.in to give
	you access to your external in the Apache/mod_jk mode. 

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/util/XsltWebXmlTask.java: Create extra
	directory for each project/host with 'hostbased webapps' enabled
	* projects/core/build/create_apacheconf.xsl: Support for project
	specific jkmount directives
	* projects/core/build/create_serverxml.xsl: Adapt appBase and 
	docBase for 'hostbased webapps'
	* skel/build-skel.xml: Added autodeploy target, which deploys all
	webapps from the autodeploy directory to the according webapp
	directory

2007-02-12  Martin Leidig  <mleidig@schlund.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/FactoryInitServlet.java: store exception
	and factory name of factory which caused initialization failure as
	the newly introduced FactoryInitException
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/ServletManager.java: check if factories
	are initialized before calling process() in callProcess() and
	throw exception if not
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/FactoryInitException.java: added specialized
	exception for factory initialization erros, keeping the factory name
	and the causing Throwable

2007-02-11  Sebastian Marsching  <sebastian.marsching@1und1.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/ExtendedContext.java: 
