2007-02-09  jtl  <jtl@schlund.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/Context.java: 
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/ContextImpl.java: 
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/app/DefaultIWrapperState.java: 
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/context/RequestContextImpl.java: 
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/AbstractXMLServer.java: remove all the latest changes. we don't try to generate an ETag 
	from the DOM anymore, as this will never work completely reliably. Instead we MD5 the (html) output. 
	* projects/core/xsl/utils.xsl: don't use __reuse=<TS> for xmlonly output. we store the relevant 
	  DOM now in a special place (only when editmode is allowed) 
	* projects/core/xsl/master.xsl: always call setNostore(true) even when in development mode

2007-02-09  Martin Leidig  <mleidig@schlund.de>

	* build.xml: Added new target srcjar, which builds a jar file
	containing the Java sources needed for debugging. The target
	is automatically executed when calling ant dist and creates an
	according pfixcore-src-{version].jar file in the dist directory

2007-02-08  Sebastian Marsching  <sebastian.marsching@1und1.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/util/UnpackModuleTask.java: 
	* projects/core/schema/moduledescriptor200702.xsd: 
	* skel/build-skel.xml: 
	Adding support for resource data in JAR libraries. The resource data will
	be copied to the projects/modules/<module-x> directory if a suitable
	deployment descriptor is present in the JAR archive.

2007-02-08  Martin Leidig  <mleidig@schlund.de>

	* build.xml: Removed exclusion of the de.skelexamples package
	from compiling (it just confuses Eclipse, which sometimes doesn't
	compile the classes and shows errors). Added exclusion of the
	packages de.schlund.pfixcore.example and de.skelexamples to the
	jar file creation target (cause they're not needed/wanted here)

2007-02-08  jtl  <jtl@schlund.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/Context.java (resetUICache): new method.
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/ContextImpl.java (resetUICache): implement it.
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/app/DefaultIWrapperState.java (getDocument): call context.resetUICache()
	when handling submitted data.
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/context/RequestContextImpl.java (handleRequest): 
	- new feature: implement a possibility to have a running timestamp in the session (and be able to reset it to the current time) 
	that is used to decide if a matching ETag results in the sending a NOT_MODIFIED header.
	- new feature: also redirect whenever the incoming page from the request isn't the page used for the UI.
	This will eliminate misleading pages visible in the URL (and wrong reload behavior) when moving ahead in a pageflow.
	(resetUICache): new method (see above).
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/ResultDocument.java (ResultDocument): use the timestamp from the 
	SPDocument for consistency
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/SPDocument.java: change all occurrences of sslredirect -> redirect
	because we not only do this for the SSL case anymore
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/perflogging/PerfEventType.java: new type for measuring
	the creation of ETags from the DOM tree

2007-02-08  Martin Leidig  <mleidig@schlund.de>

	Split include.xsl into XSLT1 and XSLT2 version, thus all 
	runtime dependencies to a specific Saxon version (caused by
	incompatible extension functions) are removed and XSLT1- or 
	XSLT2-only usage doesn't require to include both Saxon libraries.

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/util/Xslt.java: Modified the URIResolver
	to dispatch to XSLT version specific include.xsl files
	* projects/core/xsl/include.xsl: Removed XSLT2 dependent stuff
	* projects/core/xsl/include_xslt2.xsl: Added an own include.xsl
	version for XSLT2

2007-02-08  Martin Leidig  <mleidig@schlund.de>

	* build.xml: removed unnecessary dist.type=prerelease option,
	release and build suffice, build is with and release without
	svn revision as version suffix

2007-02-07  Martin Leidig  <mleidig@schlund.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/util/XsltProvider.java: Added automatic
	Saxon version availability check to avoid NoClassDefFoundErrors
	if XSLT1 or XSLT2 version isn't available.

2007-02-07  Martin Leidig  <mleidig@schlund.de>

	* projects/core/conf/server-config.wsdd: Added
	* projects/common/conf/server-config.wsdd: Removed as obsolete
	* skel/projects/common/conf/server-config.wsdd: Removed as obsolete
	* skel/build-skel.xml: Changed location of server-config.wsdd

2007-02-02  jtl  <jtl@schlund.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/generator/IWrapperImpl.java: 
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/app/IWrapperSimpleContainer.java:
	some Hash* -> Tree* to gain dependable output ordering in the DOM tree.

2007-01-30  Martin Leidig  <mleidig@schlund.de>

	Extended distribution file naming opportunities. Now you can use
	three different version naming conventions (set via the "${dist.type}"
	property in the build file or as ant parameter): "release" uses 
	"${dist.version}", "prerelease" uses "${dist.version}-pre" and
	"build" uses "${dist.version}-${dist.revision}" (svn revision) as
	version part. Default is "build", e.g. it can be overriden via
	"ant -Ddist.type=release dist". 
	   
	* build.xml

2007-01-26  Martin Leidig  <mleidig@schlund.de>

	Trim attribute now only supports boolean values, removed on/off
	option (cause someone didn't like and I don't mind)
	* projects/core/build/iwrapper.xsl	
	* projects/core/schema/interfacewrapper200401.xsd

2007-01-26  Martin Leidig  <mleidig@schlund.de>

	* projects/core/build/create_depend.xsl: fixed strange incompatibility
	between saxon and xalan transformations, which  could cause wrong output 
	encoding	

2007-01-23  Martin Leidig  <mleidig@schlund.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/targets/TargetGenerator.java: removed resetting
	of TargetGenerationReport before each generation iteration (this caused
	that generation exceptions were not reported in exception summary)
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/ImageGeometry.java: avoid NullPointerException
	if image doesn't exist, just proceed without the image information (it's
	a common case cause in a lot of projects users wrongly use attribute
	value templates within the image source attribute, which weren't yet
	evaluated at the time the extension function is called, for the sake of
	backwards compatibility we should still support this behaviour)

2007-01-23  Sebastian Marsching  <sebastian.marsching@1und1.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/editor2/core/spring/ProjectFactoryServiceImpl.java (init): 
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/editor2/frontend/util/EditorApplicationContextFactory.java: 
	Added code to handle missing <name> or <comment> tag within a project definition.
	Changed locking to ensure that an exception is thrown when the editor app is
	called but has not been initialized instead of dead-locking the thread.

2007-01-22  Martin Leidig  <mleidig@schlund.de>

	Added the optional IWrapper parameter attribute 'trim', which 
	provides the option to enable/disable the automatic trimming of 
	request parameters. The backwards compatible default behaviour, 
	in absence of the attribute, is to trim incoming parameters 
	before further processing (trim="true|false|on|off").

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/generator/IWrapperParam.java: made
	parameter trimming optional (can be set via trim argument of
	constructor)
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/generator/IWrapperIndexedParam.java:
	same as above
	* projects/core/build/iwrapper.xsl: trim attribute at param
	elements is evaluated and used as argument of for IWrapperParam 
	constructor
	* projects/core/schema/interfacewrapper200401.xsd: Added trim
	attribute at param elements to schema

2007-01-22  Martin Leidig  <mleidig@schlund.de>

	* projects/core/script/webservice_json.js: Fixed escaping of
	double quotes and backslashes.

2007-01-22  Sebastian Marsching  <sebastian.marsching@1und1.de>

	* projects/core/schema/properties200401.xsd:
	Replaced xs:all with xs:sequence to solve boundary problems.

2007-01-19  Martin Leidig  <mleidig@schlund.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/jsonws/BeanDescriptor.java: removed
	checking of getter return type against setter argument type, allow type
	discrepancy

2007-01-19  Jens Lautenbacher  <jtl@schlund.de>

	* projects/core/build/create_depend.xsl: Allow for more than one
	variant of the master and metatags file in one project by adding a
	"name" attribute to standardmaster and standardmetatags (default
	empty) and a "master" and "metatags" attribute to
	standardpage (also empty by default). Using "name" of
	standardmaster or standardmetatags results in master-NAME.xsl or
	metatags-NAME.xsl targets to be defined which can be referred to in
	standardpage by using <standardpage master="NAME" metags="NAME" ...>

2007-01-19  Sebastian Marsching  <sebastian.marsching@1und1.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/config/impl/CommonServletConfig.java: 
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/config/impl/ContextXMLServletConfigImpl.java: 
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/config/impl/DirectOutputServletConfigImpl.java: 
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/config/impl/DirectPagerequestRule.java: 
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/config/impl/ServletInfoEditModeRule.java: 
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/config/impl/ServletInfoRule.java: 
	* projects/core/schema/configfragments200609.xsd: 
	* projects/core/schema/properties200401.xsd: 
	* projects/sample1/conf/direct.conf.xml: 
	* projects/sample1/conf/fragments.xml: 
	Added support for includes in configuration for the direct output server.
	Deprecated depend and editmode configuration options for direct output server
	because the were not used.
2007-01-18  Martin Leidig  <mleidig@schlund.de>

	Added classhinting support to the JSON protocol. Classhinting can 
	be enabled/disabled within the webservice configuration file using
	the json element with the boolean classhinting attribute (globally
	or service specific). By default classhinting is disabled.

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/jsonws/JSONSerializer.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/jsonws/Bean.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/jsonws/JSONWSProcessor.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/config/ServiceConfig.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/config/GlobalServiceConfig.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/config/ConfigurationReader.java
	* projects/core/schema/wsconfig200401.xsd

2007-01-18  Martin Leidig  <mleidig@schlund.de>

	Added support for java.util.Date to JSON webservices. It's
	recommended to use java.util.Calendar instead, Date is only 
	supported for backwards compatibility (besides the SOAP services,
	resp. AXIS, don't support arrays of Dates, but work with
	Calendar arrays).

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/example/webservices/TypeTest.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/example/webservices/TypeTestImpl.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/jsonws/SerializerRegistry.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/jsonws/BeanDescriptor.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/jsonws/DeserializerRegistry.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/jsonws/serializers/BeanSerializer.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/jsonws/serializers/CalendarSerializer.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/jsonws/JSONWSProcessor.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/jsonws/deserializers/CalendarDeserializer.java
	* projects/webservice/htdocs/typetest-pfxsoap.js
	* projects/webservice/conf/webservice.conf.xml

2007-01-17  Martin Leidig  <mleidig@schlund.de>

	Added support for customizable Javascript namespaces to autogenerated
	webservice stubs (supported are custom prefixes, java-package-like
	namespaces via Javascript object scopes, backwards compatible
	namespace prefixes and usage of the Java class name).

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/ServiceRuntime.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/Constants.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/jsonws/JSONWSStubGenerator.java
