2007-01-10  Martin Leidig  <mleidig@schlund.de>

	* projects/core/script/webservice.js: fixed null value handling bug

2007-01-03  Sebastian Marsching  <sebastian.marsching@1und1.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/editor2/core/spring/PustefixSessionServiceImpl.java: 
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/editor2/frontend/util/SpringHelperEndContextInterceptor.java:
	Wrapping reference to context held by Spring bean within a WeakReference to
	make sure memory can be freed even if an unused thread still has a reference. 
	
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/exception/PustefixApplicationException.java (added): 
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/exception/PustefixCoreException.java (added): 
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/exception/PustefixException.java (added): 
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/exception/PustefixRuntimeException.java (added): 
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/scriptedflow/vm/ScriptVM.java: 
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/context/RequestContextImpl.java: 
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/Context.java: 
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/ContextImpl.java: 
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/ContextResourceManager.java: 
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/FlowStep.java: 
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/Navigation.java: 
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/NavigationFactory.java: 
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/NavigationInitializationException.java (added): 
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/jmx/TrailLogger.java: 
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/AbstractXMLServer.java: 
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/ContextXMLServer.java: 
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/RenderingException.java (added): 
	Redesigned exception handling: Context methods now throw PustefixCoreExceptions
	and PustefixApplicationExceptions instead of generic Exceptions.
	PustefixApplicationExceptions wrap exceptions thrown by application code (e.g.
	State instances).

2007-01-02  Martin Leidig  <mleidig@schlund.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/generate/WebServiceTask.java: removed check
	for webservice source files (cause they aren't really required and are absent if
	the services come from jar files), extended modification check (modtime within jar
	file is checked too)

2007-01-02  Martin Leidig  <mleidig@schlund.de>

	Added new AJAX JS stub callback mechanism. Now you can pass an object to 
	the webservice constructor and the webservice will automatically call back
	object methods of the same name.

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/generate/Wsdl2Js.java: generate JS stub
	constructors with optional callback object argument
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/generate/js/JsClass.java: added support
	to generate JS stub constructors with arguments
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/example/webservices/CallTest.java: added test 
	webservice to test all webservice call variants 
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/example/webservices/CallTestImpl.java: added
	CallTest service implementation
	* projects/core/script/webservice.js: added object callback mechanism
	
	Added webservice example application page to test all webservice call
	variants (sync, async, callback function or object, with or without 
	request id):

	* projects/webservice/txt/pages/main_calltest.xml: added
	* projects/webservice/xml/two_frames.xml: changed
	* projects/webservice/htdocs/calltest-pfxsoap.js: added
	* projects/webservice/conf/webservice.conf.xml: changed
	* projects/webservice/conf/config.conf.xml: changed

