2006-12-13  Sebastian Marsching  <sebastian.marsching@1und1.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/util/StateUtil.java (addResponseHeadersAndType): 
	Added support for global response headers that are applied to all pages.

2006-12-13   Martin Leidig  <mleidig@schlund.de>

	Added support for simultaneous usage of different XSLT processors
	and differnet XSLT versions. Supported are: Saxon/XSLT1 and Saxon/XSLT2.
	The version can be switched in depend.xml, using the xsltversion
	attribute at the root node (possible values are 1 or 2).

	Made all XSLT processing classes XSLT processor independent, the Xml,
	Xsl and XPath classes now work on interfaces which have to be implemented
	by the XSLT processors (XmlSupport, XslSupport, XPathSupport). 
	Implementations of these interfaces are managed by the XsltProvider class.
	Thus all supported XSLT processors and their libraries are only required
	at compile time. At runtime the really used processors are sufficient:

	Interfaces: 

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/util/XsltContext.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/util/XPathSupport.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/util/XsltSupport.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/util/XmlSupport.java

	Implementations:

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/util/xsltimpl/XsltSaxon1.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/util/xsltimpl/XsltSaxon2.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/util/xsltimpl/XPathSaxon1.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/util/xsltimpl/XPathSaxon2.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/util/xsltimpl/XmlSaxon1.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/util/xsltimpl/XmlSaxon2.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/util/xsltimpl/XsltContextSaxon1.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/util/xsltimpl/XsltContextSaxon2.java

	The following classes now work on the interfaces and retrieve
	the implementations using the XsltVersion:

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/util/Xml.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/util/XPath.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/util/Xslt.java

	Other changed or new XSLT classes:

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/util/XsltVersion.java: Identifies the
	used XSLT version, possible values are XsltVersion.XSLT1 for
	Saxon/XSLT1 and XsltVersion.XSLT2 for Saxon/XSLT2
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/util/XsltProvider.java: Manages XSLT
	implementations: registers only implementations which can be
	instantiated (if the according XSLT processor libraries are
	available)
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/util/XPathDefault.java: Implements the
	XPathSupport via the JAXP XPath API
	

	Some classes which were reading in Saxon's internal DOM representation,
	but only need an implementation independent W3C DOM, now are using the
	default JAXP DOM. This reduces the dependencies to the internal DOM
	representation, which now has to be specified explicitly, cause multiple
	internal DOM models can be in use. If a class requires a Saxon DOM, it
	either has to retrieve the currently configured XSLT version from the
	target generator, implement an own configuration mechanism or can get
	the preferred version via XsltProvider.getPreferredXsltVersion (in this
	case the class has to ensure that it works with all models, cause the
	preferred version can be subject to change). The following classes now
	use a JAXP DOM:

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/scriptedflow/compiler/Compiler.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/util/Cleanup.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/util/WebappCopyPassthroughHtdocsTask.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/util/GenerateSCodes.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/ProjectInitFactory.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/jmx/JmxServer.java

	Cause the method signatures of Saxon1 and Saxon2 extension functions
	containing the processor specific XPathContext aren't compatible, we
	have to provide an own version for each processor. They wrap the
	processor specific Context into a XsltContext object and thus can use
	the original extension functions:

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/IncludeDocumentExtensionSaxon1.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/IncludeDocumentExtensionSaxon2.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/ImageThemedSrcSaxon1.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/ImageThemedSrcSaxon2.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/DependencyTrackerSaxon1.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/DependencyTrackerSaxon2.java

	The following extension functions now use the abstract XsltContext
	and are used by the Saxon processor specific extension functions:

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/IncludeDocumentExtension.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/DependencyTracker.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/ImageThemedSrc.java	

	Other changes:

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/editor2/core/spring/internal/ProjectImpl.java:
	pass XsltVersion
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/Navigation.java: use passed XsltVersion
	to build internal Saxon DOM node
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/NavigationFactory.java: pass/use passed
	XsltVersion co create Navigation objects
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/util/Cleanup.java: method signature to get 
	IncludeDocument changed (set no Xslt version, which means getting a
	JAXP DOM)
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/IncludeDocumentFactory.java: use XsltVersion to
	retrieve Saxon dependent includes, add xslt version to key to allow
	caching of the same include in different DOM versions	
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/AbstractXMLServer.java: use XsltVersion to parse
	Document and retrieve Navigation
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/exceptionprocessor/UniversalExceptionProcessor.java:
	use XsltVersion to parse Document
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/IncludeDocument.java: now needs to get passed
	XsltVersion to create the appropriate document
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/targets/XMLLeafTarget.java: passes XsltVersion
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/targets/XSLLeafTarget.java: passes XsltVersion
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/targets/XMLVirtualTarget.java: passes XsltVersion
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/targets/XSLVirtualTarget.java: passes XsltVersion
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/targets/SharedLeafFactory.java: adds XsltVersion
	to key
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/targets/TargetGenerator.java: reads XsltVersion from
	depend.xml, fallback is XsltVersion.XSLT1, passes version when creating navi,
	is used by a lot of other classes to get current XsltVersion
	* tests/junit/de/schlund/pfixxml/util/XPathTest.java: Added tests, class now
	is used to test the JAXP XPath API, subclasses test the Saxon implementations
	* tests/junit/de/schlund/pfixxml/util/XPathSaxon1Test.java: test Saxon1 XPaths
	* tests/junit/de/schlund/pfixxml/util/XPathSaxon2Test.java: test Saxon2 XPaths
	* tests/junit/de/schlund/pfixxml/util/XmlTest.java: tests Saxon1, test class
	for Saxon2 should follow
	* tests/junit/de/schlund/pfixxml/util/XsltTest.java: tests Saxon2, test class
	for Saxon2 should follow
	* tests/junit/de/schlund/pfixxml/jmx/ApplicationListTest.java: now tests with
	default JAXP DOM

	Changed some XSLT files to work with Saxon1 and Saxon2 (in backwards
	compatibility mode):

	* projects/core/xsl/master.xsl: Define __contextpath despite it's only 
	evaluated/needed at runtime, cause Saxon2 doesn't allow the usage of undefined 
	variables/params, even if they aren't evaluated
	* projects/core/xsl/forminput.xsl: removed usage of undefined style variable
	* projects/core/xsl/include.xsl: now uses extension functions for both, Saxon1
	and Saxon2, and switches between them by detecting the xslt processor version
	via the builtin property xslt:version. 
	* projects/core/xsl/metatags.xsl: Define __contextpath param (see master.xsl)
	
	Added Saxon libraries for XSLT2 support:

	* lib/saxon8.jar
	* lib/saxon8-dom.jar
	* lib/saxon8-xpath.jar
	

2006-12-12  Jens Lautenbacher  <jtl@schlund.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/context/RequestContextImpl.java
	(RequestContextImpl::handleRequestWorker): move processing of end
	interceptors a bit up before the code block that finally stores
	the current values in the spdoc. This allows e.g. to set cookies
	in end interceptors.

2006-12-06   Martin Leidig  <mleidig@schlund.de> Joerg Haecker <haecker@schlund.de>

	Fixed "empty error page" problem.

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/ServletManager.java: throw ServletException if 
	response not committed by ExceptionProcessor
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/exceptionprocessor/ExceptionProcessor.java: documentation

2006-12-05  Sebastian Marsching  <sebastian.marsching@1und1.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/editor2/frontend/util/Diff.java (diff): 
	Fixed problem in diff algorithm causing parts at the end of a file
	to be lost at compare operation.

2006-12-01  Sebastian Marsching  <sebastian.marsching@1und1.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/editor2/core/spring/internal/CommonIncludePartThemeVariantImpl.java (setXML): 
	Changed code to create xmlns declarations in root node only, when the 
	corresponding prefix is used in at least one part.
	
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/editor2/frontend/util/Diff.java: 
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/editor2/frontend/util/DiffUtil.java: 
	Replaced diff algorithm with own implementation.

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/util/TransformerCallback.java: 
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/context/RequestContextImpl.java: 
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/AbstractXMLServer.java: 
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/ContextXMLServer.java: 
	Moved responsibility for setting the right RequestContext when
	rendering a document from TransformerCallback to ContextXMLServer.
	ContextXMLServer now uses hooks supplied by AbstractXMLServer before and
	after rendering a XML document to create a copy of the RequestContextImpl
	used to create a SPDocument and sets this copy for the current thread,
	thus avoiding concurrency problems when different views of the
	same document are rendered concurrently (e.g. frames).

2006-11-29  Jens Lautenbacher  <jtl@schlund.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/AbstractXMLServer.java (AbstractXMLServer):
	cosmetics, removed (some) unused variables

