	* projects/core/xsl/master.xsl: not yet ready changes to maybe
	support customizing the excluded namespace prefixes
	
2006-08-15  Sebastian Marsching  <sebastian.marsching@1und1.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/ContextImpl.java: 
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/serverutil/SessionHelper.java: 
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/ServletManager.java: 
	* projects/common/conf/pustefix.xml: 
	Rewriting SSL redirect to support non-default SSL ports. Now a
	pfixcore.ssl_redirect_port.for.<HTTP port> property can be set
	in common/conf/pustefix.xml to specify a SSL port corresponding
	to the used HTTP port.

