2006-07-17  Sebastian Marsching  <sebastian.marsching@1und1.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/ServletManager.java (tryReloadProperties): 
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/config/ContextConfig.java (setProperties): 
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/config/ContextXMLServletConfig.java (readFromFile): 
	Changed ContextConfig to take a reference to a Properties object instead of
	creating its own thus allowing modifications to the object to propagate to
	the context. Reintroduced special property "__PROPERTIES_LOAD_INDEX".
	
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/config/ServletManagerConfig.java (setProperties): 
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/config/PageRequestConfig.java (setProperties): 
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/config/DirectOutputPageRequestConfig.java (setProperties): 
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/config/ContextConfig.java (setProperties): 
	Changing setProperties() methods to copy each property instead of using the
	given Properties object as the parent for the new one as this caused problems
	with buggy code using the inappropriate Properties#get(Object) method instead
	of Properties#getProperty(String)

