	* stuff/migration-tool/src/do_migration.sh: 
	Fixing classpath problems
	
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/ContextXMLServer.java (getDom): 
	Moved check for VM exit state in finally block, so it is honored even
	if an exception is thrown
	
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/scriptedflow/vm/ScriptVM.java (run): 
	Made sure that scripted flow is canceled when an exception occurs

2006-07-07  Martin Leidig  <mleidig@schlund.de>

	Added support for JSON as (web)service protocol. It can be
	used just as a SOAP service: you just have to instantiate a
	stub and can call the remote methods. In contrast to SOAP stubs
	the JSON stubs are Dynamic Proxies which request the method
	descriptions from the server and dynamically create according
	Javascript methods. JSON and SOAP stubs are largely compatible
	for the caller, so they can be used together and migrating in
	between should work without code changes.

	Introduced general service runtime and processing layer, into
	which different service protocols can be plugged by implementing
	the ServiceProcessor interface.
	Refactored monitoring and logging facilities. Made them service
	independent and transparent for service processors. Authentication
	now also is done on service runtime level (removed all special
	handling within according Axis request/response handlers).
	Refactored the webservice configuration system, now it's completely
	XML based, no more property stuff.
	The JSON services use parts of the JSON-RPC framework for
	serialization/deserialization. Added some patches to it: fixed
	problem with float number precision in the included json.org code,
	moved the org.json package down in the package hierarchy to 
	support other implementations, added support for sending the
	exceptions names as part of the JSON response.
	Integrated the JSON framework: added special Date handler for
	Calendar support (compatibility with SOAP-Java-Binding). 
	Implemented general service registry mechanism for service
	description and instance creation/management.

	Refactored all webservice sample applications, added switchable 
	support for SOAP and JSON protocol, removed proprietary/browser
	dependent stuff. 
	

	Added:

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/ServiceDescriptor.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/ServiceProcessor.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/ServiceCallContext.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/ServiceRuntime.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/HttpServiceRequest.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/ServiceRequest.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/ServiceRequestWrapper.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/ServiceProcessingException.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/HttpServiceResponse.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/ServiceResponse.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/ServiceException.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/ServiceResponseWrapper.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/utils
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/utils/RecordingReader.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/utils/XMLFormatter.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/utils/RecordingRequestWrapper.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/utils/RecordingInputStream.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/utils/RecordingOutputStream.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/utils/RecordingWriter.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/utils/RecordingResponseWrapper.java
