2006-07-04  Jens Lautenbacher  <jtl@schlund.de>

	* projects/core/xsl/master.xsl: make sure that $navitree is also
	valid in the final generated stylesheet (that means: at runtime)
	so it's still possible to iterate over the pages in runtime code.

	* projects/sample1/txt/pages/main_home.xml: fix accordingly (use
	$navitree//pages instead of /formresult/navigation//pages)

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/Context.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/ContextImpl.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/app/DefaultAuthIWrapperState.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/app/DefaultIWrapperState.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/app/StaticState.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/context/SessionContextImpl.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/AbstractXMLServer.java: removed all the
	navigation generating and handling stuff

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/SessionCleaner.java: 
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/AbstractXMLServer.java: changed to handle
	storing of more than one SPDocument in a LRUCache, make sure that
	they are cleared with a TimerTask when needed and other little
	fixes to make the callback to not store a spdoc work in the case
	of an SSL redirect. 

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/ContextImpl.java
	(ContextImpl::handleRequest): set the Context as a xslt param in
	the spdoc.
	(ContextImpl::handleRequestWorker): no longer synchronized.
	(ContextImpl::isPageAccessible): synchronize if config says so.
	(ContextImpl::isPageAccessibleWorker): used from mthod above.
	(ContextImpl::isPageAlreadyVisited): new method: check to see if
	page has already been visited in this session.

	* projects/core/xsl/master.xsl: 2 new params __context__ and
	__spdoc__ containing opaque java objects used in callbacks. 
	Set the nostore flag in the spdoc whenever we don't use frames AND
	$prohibitEdit != 'no'.

	* projects/core/xsl/navigation.xsl: 
	* projects/core/xsl/forminput.xsl: use callbacks instead of /formresult/navigation

	* projects/core/xsl/xmlfontify.xsl: no longer handle /formresult/navigation

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/util/TransformerCallback.java: new
	class, used as XSLT callbacks

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/context/AccessibilityChecker.java
	(AccessibilityChecker::isPageAlreadyVisited): new method

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/util/SimpleCacheLRU.java: new
	class. Implement a LRU Cache with a remove method...

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/util/Xslt.java (Xslt::transform): 	
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/ContextXMLServer.java (ContextXMLServer::getDom): cosmetics

