	a compatibility layer for applications. Removed AuthContext as now the 
	Context implementation is bound to the ContextXMLServer and cannot be replaced
	by an application anymore.

2006-06-13  Jens Lautenbacher  <jtl@schlund.de>

	* projects/sample1/txt/pages/*: 
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/example/*:  added some more tests

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/Context.java (Context): store
	the jumptopage and jumptopageflow not as PageRequest and PageFlow
	but as Strings instead. This way we can select the right variant
	just before we use them. In other news, when a jumptopageflow
	isn't given, the isJumpToPageFlowSet() returns null, not the
	"default" pageflow. When it is set, we also set the
	isCurrentPageFlowRequestedByUser to true when we finally use the
	jumptopageflow in documentFromFlow(), if it is null the "right"
	pageflow is selected automatically via the usual rules.

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/FlowStepSetFlowAction.java (FlowStepSetFlowAction::setData): 
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/FlowStepJumpToAction.java (FlowStepJumpToAction::setData): 
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/FlowStepForceStopAction.java (FlowStepForceStopAction::setData): 
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/FlowStepAction.java
	(setData::data): use HashMap<String, String>

