2006-05-29  Sebastian Marsching <sebastian.marsching@1und1.de>

	* Starting development version 0.9.1-pre

	* Releasing version 0.9.0

2006-05-29  Jens Lautenbacher  <jtl@schlund.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/Context.java: cleanup. Setting
	of variants in preparation for request/session state split. 

2006-05-26  Martin Leidig  <mleidig@schlund.de>

	Added support for unsynchronized (on the Context) webservice calls.
	Therefore introduced new 'synchronize'-attribute (true|false) at the
	'context'-element in the webservice configuration file. For backwards
	compatibility reasons 'true' (enabled synchronization) is default.
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/WebServiceServlet.java: Added
	case switch for synchronization
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/config/ServiceConfig.java: Added
	'synchronize' property
	* projects/core/schema/wsconfig200401.xsd: Added 'synchronize' attribute

2006-05-22  Martin Leidig  <mleidig@schlund.de>

	Resolved the filename encoding problem relating to form-based file
	uploads. Replaced the javax.mail.internet.InternetHeaders class by
	an own RFC 822 message header parser. Due to the fact that current
	browsers don't encode non-ASCII characters (as they should do and
	as defined in RFC 1522), but send the raw bytes in the encoding of
	the page, the parser decodes the bytes according to the specified
	character encoding.

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/multipart/RFC822Headers.java: Parser for
	RFC 822 headers
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/multipart/MultipartHandler.java: Replaced
	InternetHeaders class by RFC822Headers class
	* tests/junit/de/schlund/pfixxml/multipart/RFC822HeadersTest.java:
	Added some tests for different headers and browsers (and recorded
	upload requests in .dump files)
	* tests/junit/de/schlund/pfixxml/multipart/ff_win_upload.dump
	* tests/junit/de/schlund/pfixxml/multipart/ff_linux_upload.dump
	* tests/junit/de/schlund/pfixxml/multipart/ie_win_upload.dump
	* tests/junit/de/schlund/pfixxml/multipart/complex_header.dump

2006-05-22  Sebastian Marsching  <sebastian.marsching@1und1.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/Context.java: 
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/PageFlowManager.java: 
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/AbstractXMLServer.java: 
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/SessionCleaner.java: 
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/SPDocument.java: 
	Redesigned SSL switch handling. Now when a SSL-enabled page
	is requested through the pageflow, a redirect is triggered
	to switch the connection to SSL. After the switch, the stored
	SPDocument is used to serve the request. To make this work
	SPDocument does not implemenet NoCopySessionData.
	Context now uses the new PageFlowManager#getPageFlowByName(String, Variant)
	method to make the code readable more easily.

2006-05-17  Sebastian Marsching  <sebastian.marsching@1und1.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/VariantManager.java (getVariantMatchingPageFlowName): 
	Fixing bug in VariantManager causing to return non-existent variants
	of a pageflow

2006-05-15  Sebastian Marsching  <sebastian.marsching@1und1.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/VariantManager.java: 
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/PageFlowManager.java: 
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/Context.java: 
	Moved variant handling for pageflows from PageFlowManager
	to VariantManager. Optimized PageFlowManager by reducing
	number of pageflows being searched for page
	
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/config/ContextConfig.java (getPageFlowConfig): 
	Added method to get config for a specific pageflow

