	to context class to prepare for removal of PageRequestProperties

2006-05-12  Jens Lautenbacher  <jtl@schlund.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/Context.java (Context): made private.
	(Context::documentFromFlow): move the logic to stay on the current
	page if the page is neither part of the pageflow nor the pageflow
	has been explicitely set by the client for this request into the
	context's pageflow handling.

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/app/DefaultIWrapperState.java
	(canContinue): removed. We want to aggregate such logic in the
	Context instead.
	(DefaultIWrapperState::getDocument): use
	context.stateMustSupplyFullDocument() instead of canContinue()
	here. 

2006-05-12  Sebastian Marsching  <sebastian.marsching@1und1.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/app/DefaultIWrapperState.java (getIHandlerContainer): 
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/app/IHandlerContainerManager.java (init): 
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/Context.java: 
	Using ContextConfig instead of Context object to reduce number
	of IHandlerContainerManagers (saves memory)

2006-05-10  Sebastian Marsching  <sebastian.marsching@1und1.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/App/DefaultIWrapperState.java (getIHandlerContainer): 
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/App/IHandlerContainerManager.java (init): 
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/ContextXMLServer.java (tryReloadProperties): 
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/PropertyObjectManager.java: 
	Changed IHandlerContainerManager to take a dummy Context object during
	initialization in order to fix problems with IHandlerContainerManager being
	inadvertently shared across contexts. Removed getPropertyObject(...) methods from
	PropertyObjectManager as the cause for this bug was an unclean implemenation of
	equals() in the Properties class.

