	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/ConfigurableObject.java: 
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/ContextXMLServer.java: 
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/DerefServer.java: 
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/DirectOutputServlet.java: 
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/FactoryInitServlet.java: 
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/PropertyObjectManager.java: 
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/ServletManager.java: 
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/ServletManagerCompat.java: 
	* example/common/conf/apploader.xml: 
	* example/common/conf/exceptionhandler.xml: 
	* example/common/conf/pfixlog.xml: 
	* example/common/conf/factory.xml: 
	* example/common/conf/pustefix.xml: 
	* example/core/editor2/conf/depend.xml: 
	* example/core/editor2/conf/edit.conf.xml: 
	* example/sample1/conf/config.conf.xml: 
	* example/sample1/conf/depend.xml: 
	* example/sample1/conf/direct.conf.xml: 
	* example/sample1/conf/project.xml.in: 
	* example/sample1/conf/secure.conf.xml: 
	* example/servletconf/projects.xml.in: 
	* example/simpleform/conf/config.conf.xml: 
	* example/simpleform/conf/depend.xml: 
	* example/simpleform/conf/project.xml.in: 
	* example/simplelink/conf/config.conf.xml: 
	* example/simplelink/conf/depend.xml: 
	* example/simplelink/conf/project.xml.in: 
	* example/simplepage/conf/config.conf.xml: 
	* example/simplepage/conf/depend.xml: 
	* example/simplepage/conf/project.xml.in: 
	* example/webservice/conf/config.conf.xml: 
	* example/webservice/conf/depend.xml: 
	* example/webservice/conf/webservice.conf.xml: 
	* example/webservice/conf/project.xml.in: 
	* skel/projects/common/conf/apploader.xml: 
	* skel/projects/common/conf/exceptionhandler.xml: 
	* skel/projects/common/conf/factory.xml: 
	* skel/projects/common/conf/pfixlog.xml: 
	* skel/projects/common/conf/pustefix.xml: 
	* skel/projects/servletconf/projects.xml.in: 
	* skel/build-skel.xml: 
	* skel/newproject.sh: 
	* build.xml: 
	Rewrote configuration system: Now all configuration files (except projects.xml)
	are directly read at runtime and do not require any additional generation
	step. In order to improve compatibility with old applications a new class
	"ServletManagerCompat" was introduced which can be used to derive class that
	were previously derived from "ServletManager". This compatibility class
	reads a configuration file in the XML properties file format.

2006-03-08  Jens Lautenbacher  <jtl@schlund.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/util/Xslt.java (Xslt::createIdentityTransformer): re-enabled 
	synchronization for testing purposes...

2006-03-07  Martin Leidig  <mleidig@schlund.de>

	* example/core/build/create_serverxml.xsl: Set useBodyEncodingForURI also for standalone 
	connectors (fixes special character problems for GET requests in standalone mode)

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/multipart/MultipartHandler.java: Request parameter parsing now
	uses the encoding provided by the underlying ServletRequest (fixes special character
	problems for multipart form parameters on non-ISO-8859-1-pages, but doesn't fix the
	decoding problem with non-ISO-8859-1 filenames in den Content-Disposition header)	

	Added encoding test example for multipart form handling and file upload
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/example/iwrapper/EncodingTest.iwrp
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/example/iwrapper/EncodingTestUpload.iwrp
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/example/ContextEncodingTestImpl.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/example/EncodingTestUploadHandler.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/example/ContextEncodingTest.java
	* example/sample1/txt/pages/main_encoding.xml
	* example/sample1/conf/config.prop.in

