2006-01-31  Sebastian Marsching  <sebastian.marsching@1und1.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/lucefix/IncludeFileHandler.java: 
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/editor2/core/spring/internal/CommonIncludePartImpl.java: 
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/editor2/core/spring/internal/CommonIncludePartThemeVariantImpl.java: 
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/editor2/frontend/resources/CommonIncludesResourceImpl.java (getContent): 
	Renamed "product" tag to "theme" in editor code, removed default language node
	in template for new include parts

2006-01-31  Jens Lautenbacher  <jtl@schlund.de>

	* */txt/*.xml, */dyntxt/*.xml: New format for include parts: "product is now called "theme", and the 
	language nodes are removed (whenever there was more than <lang name="default">, we replaced it with the 
	equivalent construct <pfx:langselect><pfx:lang name="...">....).
	
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/IncludeDocumentExtension.java (Module): 
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/DependencyTracker.java (Module): change "product" => "theme" where needed. Cleanup.

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/util/DelLang.java (Module): added. Used to convert include parts to the new format
	(product => theme, removed lang nodes)

2006-01-30  Sebastian Marsching  <sebastian.marsching@1und1.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/editor2/core/spring/internal/CommonIncludePartImpl.java: 
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/lucefix/PfixQueueManager.java (run): 
	Fixed NullPointerException
	
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/editor2/frontend/resources/CommonIncludesResourceImpl.java (setContent): 
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/editor2/core/spring/internal/CommonIncludePartThemeVariantImpl.java (setXML):
	Improved indention in CMS so that files written by CMS look more beautiful
	when they are directly edited on the filesystem. Use one constant for theme tag
	name to be prepared for changing it from "product" to "theme".

2006-01-30  Sebastian Marsching <sebastian.marsching@1und1.de>

	* Beginning new development version 0.8.10-pre

	* Releasing version 0.8.9

2006-01-27  Jens Lautenbacher  <jtl@schlund.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/generator/IWrapperIndexedParam.java (IWrapperIndexedParam::initValueFromRequest): 
	we need to check for a parameter name if it starts with "SomeName." not "SomeName" to be sure that we 
	have a indexed parameter! Shame on me, that's a very old one...

2006-01-26  Martin Leidig  <mleidig@schlund.de>

	* ./example/core/build/create_defaultwebxml.xsl: Now works again (also for Tomcat 5.5+).
	Fixed element matching problem for web-apps version 2.4 (with xsd and namespaces, which
	were not handled by the old xsl template)

2006-01-24  Sebastian Marsching  <sebastian.marsching@1und1.de>

	* example/core/editor2/txt/util_includes.xml: Fixed problem with
	include part names containing a "--"

2006-01-21  Jens Lautenbacher  <jtl@schlund.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/ServletManager.java (ServletManager::doCookieTest): 
	check the session if it's already marked and then only look for a test cookie with _any_ value,
	else we need to make sure the right value is there
	(ServletManager::createTestCookie): the cookie now always has the same name, the value is a random value.
	(ServletManager::doGet): no longer to mark the sesison here. 

