	Removed synchronized flag as the TransformerFactory.newTransformer() method
	seems to be usable concurrently by different threads

2005-12-21  Sebastian Marsching  <sebastian.marsching@1und1.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/editor2/core/spring/internal/TargetPfixImpl.java (getAffectedPages): 
	Fixed NullPointer exception in logging code
	
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/AbstractXMLServer.java (handleDocument): 
	Reenabled code that creates a Saxon Document from another DOM Document in
	order to fix strang NullPointerExceptions being thrown by Saxon on
	pages that use frames
	
	* skel/projects/common/conf/editor-spring.xml: Incorporated changes
	already present in example/common/conf/editor-spring.xml
	
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/editor2/frontend/resources/CommonIncludesResource.java:
	Added methods used by XMLRPC states to retrieve / set the collapsed/expanded
	state for the include parts tree.
	
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/editor2/frontend/resources/CommonIncludesResourceImpl.java: 
	Added code to store collapsed/expanded state of the include parts tree. This
	is mainly used to keep the client view state across several requests.
	
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/editor2/frontend/resources/DynIncludesResourceImpl.java (getIncludeFilesInDirectory): 
	Added method which returns all include files in a directory
	(getIncludePartsInFile): Added method returning all include parts in a file
	
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/editor2/frontend/resources/IncludesResourceImpl.java (getIncludeFilesInDirectory): 
	Added method which returns all include files in a directory
	(getIncludePartsInFile): Added method returning all include parts in a file

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/editor2/frontend/webservice/CommonIncludeState.java: 
	Added abstract base class for state providing XMLRPC methods for interactive
	javascript (include parts tree).
	
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/editor2/frontend/webservice/DynamicIncludesState.java: 
	Added concrete implementation of CommonIncludeState for DynIncludeParts.
	
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/editor2/frontend/webservice/StaticIncludesState.java: 
	Added concrete implementation of CommonIncludeState for static IncludeParts
	
	* example/core/editor2/conf/depend.xml.in: Added targets for pages
	ws_includes and ws_dynincludes
	
	* example/core/editor2/conf/edit.prop.in: Added page ws_includes
	and ws_dynincludes needed by javascript / XMLRPC stuff
	
	* example/core/editor2/txt/pages/main_dynincludes.xml: Added javascript
	code to set global variable containing page name.
	
	* example/core/editor2/txt/pages/main_includes.xml: Added javascript
	code to set global variable containing page name.
	
	* example/core/editor2/txt/styles.xml: Added styles needed by new 
	javascript includes tree stuff.	Fixed bug in class ".core_errorlabel_td".
	
	* example/core/editor2/txt/util_includes.xml: Display include tree
	using javascript instead of statically creating complete tree and
	hiding unneeded parts
	 
	* example/core/editor2/xml/webservice.xml: Added simple page
	master that is used to render output from webservice pages to
	XML code that can be processed by XMLHttpRequest javascript code.
	
	* example/core/script/editor.js: Complete rewrite of 
	code for include part tree: No an object model that communicates
	with the server using XMLHttpRequest is being used.
	
	* example/core/txt/styles.xml: Fixed bug in class "core_errorlabel_td",
	which was using the non-existant "align" property instead of
	"text-align".

2005-12-20 Michael Bruns <michael.bruns@schlund.de>
	* skel/build-skel.xml: fixed target extract-modules
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/ContextResourceManager.java: made getResourceIterator() public

2005-12-14  Joerg Haecker <haecker@schlund.de>

	* Changes in package src/de/schlund/pfixxml/jmx
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/jmx/Environment.java (create):
	set 'jmx.remote.tls.need.client.authentication' to 'false' if not
	secure.
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/jmx/JmxServerFactory.java: rewrite
	of port and host confifuration(see below)
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/jmx/JmxServer.java (start): more logging,
	do only check client cert if a path to keystore is passed.
	* example/common/conf/factory.prop.in:
	o removed 'de.schlund.pfixcore.jmx.port2.directory': not needed any more
	o added property 'de.schlund.pfixcore.jmx.keystore': if set use it,
	else server will be started without client auth.
	o added property 'de.schlund.pfixcore.jmx.port.default': if set use
	it, else scan for properties 'de.schlund.pfixcore.jmx.port.XX' and
	'de.schlund.pfixcore.jmx.regex.XX'. The value of port XX will be 
	used when regex.XX mathes to your docroot. Needed when running
	more than one pustefix-jvm on the same host.
	o added property 'de.schlund.pfixcore.jmx.servername': if set use it,
	else start server on localhost.
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/jmx/JMXConnectionListener.java: added
	* skel/projects/common/conf/factory.prop.in: examples added
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/FactoryInitServlet.java: PROP_DOCROOT now
	public.

2005-12-09  Jens Lautenbacher  <jtl@schlund.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/AbstractXMLServer.java (AbstractXMLServer::handleDocument):
	remove the optimisation(?) to create the tinytree from the xerces
	dom outside of the saxon transformer - this only made sense for documents that were to be reused, anyway (frames)
	Removing the stuff allows for avoiding a synchronized block in getting the identity transformer.
	
2005-12-08  Joerg Haecker <haecker@schlund.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/perflogging/AdditionalTrailInfo.java: added
	method reset()
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/perflogging/DefaultAdditionalTrailInfoImpl.java: 
	implemented reset() method
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/AbstractXMLServer.java (process): Call
	reset on AdditionalTrailInfo implementors. 

2005-12-08  Jens Lautenbacher  <jtl@schlund.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/targets/TargetDependencyRelation.java: cosmetics, (a bit of) javadoc

2005-12-07  Jens Lautenbacher  <jtl@schlund.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/targets/TargetDependencyRelation.java (module):
	fixed the bug in child->parent mapping.  Nevertheless, it is still
	commented out, because it takes a lot of memory, and is not used
	currently anyway (about 100M for around 50000 AuxDependencies!)

2005-12-06  Sebastian Marsching  <sebastian.marsching@1und1.de>

	* example/core/editor2/txt/util_includes.xml: Hide directory tree
	with include parts by default, to accelerate page loading
	
	* example/common/conf/editor-spring.xml: 
	Added property "targetfactory" to "projectfactory" bean and
	"themefactory" to "pagefactory" bean
	
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/targets/TargetGenerator.java: 
	Added support for event listeners listening for events fired when
	the configuration of the target generator changes
	
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/event/ConfigurationChangeListener.java: 
	Created event listener for configuration change events
	
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/event/ConfigurationChangeEvent.java: 
	Created event class for configuration changes
	
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/editor2/core/spring/TargetFactoryServiceImpl.java: 
	Removed usage of Hashtable and use HashMap or WeakHashMap instead.
	
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/editor2/core/spring/ProjectFactoryServiceImpl.java: 
	Added property targetfactory which is set by the Spring application context
	
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/editor2/core/spring/PageFactoryServiceImpl.java: 
	Added new property themefactory which receives a reference to the
	ThemeFactoryService from the Spring application context
	
