	AUX->(AUX) as parent<->child and Target->AUX->(AUX) as parent<->child, but depending on the target.
	Also implemented all the needed accessor methods.
	
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/targets/TargetGenerator.java (Module): removed all traces of DependencyRefCounter
	(TargetGenerator::tryReinit): call TargetDependencyRelation.resetAllRelations(...) for all current targets before 
	trying to reload the configuration.

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/targets/TargetImpl.java: 
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/targets/Target.java: cosmetics

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/targets/DependencyType.java (DependencyType::newInstance): removed method

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/targets/DependencyRefCounter.java (Module): remove

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/targets/AuxDependencyManager.java: put all the book keeping into
	the TargetDependencyRelation class. Use the methods from there and simplify the whole class.

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/targets/AuxDependencyFactory.java (AuxDependencyFactory::getAuxDependency): 
	directly create the new AuxDependency, not via the type object (what stupid idea was that???)

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/targets/AuxDependency.java: remove all the book keeping of affected
	targets, target generators and children. All this is being taken care of by the new
	TargetDependencyRelation class.
	
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/util/CheckIncludes.java (CheckIncludes::checkForUnavailableIncludes): 
	use TargetDependencyRelation
	(CheckIncludes::checkForUnavailableIncludes): use aux.getTheme()

