	Added columns for username and selected include part to list of sessions
	
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/editor2/frontend/util/EditViewResetContextInterceptor.java: 
	Created an interceptor that resets the flag indicating that an user is
	editing an include part. This is needed to make sure this flag is unset,
	whenever a user is switching to another page
	
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/editor2/frontend/util/ContextStore.java: 
	Created singleton class storing all contexts which are logged into
	the editor as keysin a WeakHashMap with the corresponding username as their
	values..
	
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/editor2/frontend/resources/SessionResourceImpl.java: 
	Implemented methods from interface (see below)
	
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/editor2/frontend/resources/SessionResource.java (isUserLoginsAllowed): 
	Added methods isIncludeEditView() and setIncludeEditView() to interface. These methods
	are used to set the flag indicating wheter a user is editing an include part
	
