2005-11-25  Jens Lautenbacher  <jtl@schlund.de>

	* example/core/xsl/*.xsl.in: removed documentation, moved to *.xsl  

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/targets/TargetDependencyRelation.java: new class. This will be the centralized
	location where we hold all target<->AuxDependency relations (will replace DependencyRefCounter and the
	reference counting of Targets and TargetGenerators in the AuxDependencies themself)

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/targets/DependencyRefCounter.java: fix email address

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/targets/Target.java (Target): make sure the interface itself extends Comparable

2005-11-24  Jens Lautenbacher  <jtl@schlund.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/targets/AuxDependency.java: more generics work. Some cosmetics like moving 
	methods around.
	(AuxDependency::removeTargetDependency): renamed from resetTargetDependency(...)

	(AuxDependency::getChildrenForThemes) 
	(AuxDependency::removeChildren): changed to no longer create empty entries for a Themes list 
	when not needed and also remove the whole entry whenever the associated Set becomes empty.

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/targets/AuxDependencyManager.java (AuxDependencyManager::getMaxTimestamp): changed 
	to no rely on a recursive check over the "top level" AuxDependencies and their children, but instead
	use the whole set as given from the DependencyRefCounter to iterate over.
	Also removed bogus boolean argument - it hasn't been used anyway.
	(AuxDependencyManager::lookForTimestamp): removed 
	
	(AuxDependencyManager::reset): changed according to above

	(AuxDependencyManager::saveAuxdepend): also changed to take into account that the recursive
	stepping through the direct AuxDeps and their children is not reliable. We make sure that at
	least ever AuxDep is saved to the .aux file once by first using the recursive loop (to save
	as much as possible from the parent-child relationship) but drag a HashSet of all
	AuxDeps (as being given by the DependencyRefCounter) along where we remove every handled
	AuxDep. After that, the potentially remaining AuxDeps in this set will be used to save them
	to the .aux file, too.

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/targets/VirtualTarget.java (VirtualTarget::needsUpdate)
	(VirtualTarget::getModTimeMaybeUpdate): changed according to above.

2005-11-23  Sebastian Marsching  <sebastian.marsching@1und1.de>

