	handleSubmittedData(): Handle SAXException instead of TransformerException
	(see above)

2005-11-23  Jens Lautenbacher  <jtl@schlund.de>

	* example/sample1/txt/navigation.xml: cosmetics

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/targets/AuxDependencyManager.java (AuxDependencyManager::reset): fixed stupid bug.
	we don't call resetTargetDependency(...) only on the direct children, but on ALL AuxDependencies that are used
	by the target. For this to work the two changes below needed to be made:

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/targets/DependencyRefCounter.java (DependencyRefCounter::getDependenciesForTarget): 
	new method, return all AuxDependencies the Target uses. 

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/targets/AuxDependency.java 
	(AuxDependency): use generics and RefCountingCollection for the reference count of targetgenerators 
	(AuxDependency::resetTargetDependency): we no longer recurse into
	the children of the AuxDependency and call resetTargetDependency(...) on them, because the
	AuxDependencyManger now loops over ALL AuxDependencies without the
	need to follow the children tree.  The old behaviour didn't work
	because it possibly left stale references to targets in
	AuxDependencies that can no longer be reached by the child tree of
	the target when it is rebuild.
	(AuxDependency::toStringShort): new method
	(AuxDependency::addTargetDependency): fixed a stupid bug with refcounting targetgenerators: Only 
	increment the generator count when the target has not already been added to the dependency's affectedtarget 
	list. This way, using the same include more than once on a target will correctly increment the
	generator ref count only by 1.

2005-11-22  Jens Lautenbacher  <jtl@schlund.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/ServletManager.java (ServletManager::doGet): supply running valid session to doCookieTest
	or the secure child session when current sessid is invalid, but a parent to a ssl session.
	(ServletManager::redirectToSecureSSLSession): call createTestCookie (shoudn't do anything most of the time,
	the cookie name in the session should be present and the cookie itself already set)
	(ServletManager::redirectToInsecureSSLSession): see above.
	(ServletManager::forceRedirectBackToInsecureSSL): test against a cokie name from the child session if present,
	only put the attribute in the current session - create the cookie if nothing is found.
	(ServletManager::forceNewSessionSameVisit): see above
	(ServletManager::redirectToSession): create the test cookie
	(ServletManager::doCookieTest): new argument session needed - this is the sesssion to look for 
	the name of the test cookie (always of the form __PFIX_TST_12345243345) to check. We only check here,
	no longer create a test cookie!
	(ServletManager::createTestCookie): new method. Called whenever we need to make sure that a test cookie has been set.

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/util/Xslt.java (FileResolver::resolve): use TargetType

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/serverutil/SessionAdmin.java (SessionAdmin::toString): cosmetics

