2005-10-20  Jens Lautenbacher  <jtl@schlund.de>

	* skel/build.xml: changed to put all generated src files (.iwrp=>.java, StatusCodeLib) into
	their own top level directory "gensrc" (accessible in ant as ${dir.gensr}). 
	The ant target "clean" simply removes this directory, the compile target has this directory 
	as an addition component of the src path. 

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/app/RequestDataImpl.java (RequestDataImpl): use the root name 
	of the pagerequest for the page name, not the name (or commands for variant pages wouldn't work)

2005-10-19  Jens Lautenbacher  <jtl@schlund.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/util/GenerateSCodes.java (Module): added. New ant task used
	to generate a class de.schlund.util.statuscodes.StatusCodeLib that holds public static fields 
	for all known StatusCodes. This gives us compile time check for unknown StatusCodes and of course
	completion in IDEs.

	* src/de/schlund/util/statuscodes/StatusCodeFactory.java (testStatusCode): changed
	to no longer get StatusCodes from PartIndex, but instead look at the generated 
	StatusCodeLib class via reflection if a StatusCode exists.
	(getStatusCode): no longer need to catch transfomer exceptions

	* src/de/schlund/util/statuscodes/PartIndex.java (Module): removed. no longer needed to
	dynamically load StatusCodes.

	* skel/build.xml: new target scgenerate to generate a list of
	public static final fields of all StatusCodes known.  make targets
	"compile" and "compile-xml" depend on it. make "scgenerate" depend
	on "propfiles"

	* example/core/dyntxt/statusmessages.xml: one more scode, fixed a description text

	* skel/projects/common/conf/factory.prop.in: 
	* example/common/conf/factory.prop.in: remove starting of PartIndex
	factory, remove no longer used partindex.reloadchanges
	property. partindex.scodefile.* stays as it is. In the skel version of factory.prop.in,
	use the new definitions from the example versions for perfstat.

	* build.xml: inlcude GenerateSCodes in the classes to build as ant tasks

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/editor/EditorCommonsFactory.java : cosmetics

