	* skel/build.xml: merge core/dyntxt/statusmessages.xml into common/dyntxt/statusmessages-core-merged.xml

	* skel/projects/common/dyntxt/statusmessages.xml (Module): is now empty.

	* build.xml: remove inclusion of common subdirectory in data file.

	* skel/projects/common/dyntxt/statusmessages-core-merged.xml (Module): new file in all 
	environments: CAUTION! this must be copied when updating old environments! SCodes from core
	will be merged into this file.

	* src/de/schlund/util/statuscodes/PartIndex.java (PartFile): new inner class. Holds a file that
	contains statuscodes and the file modification time when the file was loaded last.
	(Module): rewrote to handle more than one statuscode file. Initialises the StatusCodes with
	part name and path to their origin file.

	* src/de/schlund/util/statuscodes/StatusCode.java (StatusCode): constructor now needs
	an additional Path argument to the corresponding include part file.
	(getStatusCodePath): new method.

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/ResultDocument.java (createIncludeFromStatusCode): don't get the 
	path to the statuscode's include part from a property but from the SCode itself.

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/editor/EditorCommonsFactory.java: 
	(init): automatically use all defined partindex statuscode files.

	* skel/projects/common/conf/factory.prop.in: 
	* example/common/conf/factory.prop.in: add partindex.scodefile entries. 
	There's no need any more to repeat them in "editorcommonsfactory.includefile", they are 
	automatically used there. Only other, non-StatusCode dynamic include files should be added
	via editorcommonsfactory.includefile.

	* skel/projects/common/conf/pustefix.prop.in:
	* example/common/conf/pustefix.prop.in:  remove statuscodefactory.messagefile

	* example/common/dyntxt/statusmessages.xml (Module): removed, splitted into the next 
	two new files. Only the "core" one is relevant for pustefix skeleton environments 
	* example/sample1/dyntxt/statusmessages.xml (Module): new.
	* example/core/dyntxt/statusmessages.xml (Module): new.

	* example/sample1/txt/pages/main_scripting.xml: cosmetics

