	know on which cluster we will land - so now we use a property from pustefix.prop

2005-08-06  Jens Lautenbacher  <jtl@schlund.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/DerefServer.java: now sign the encoded link so we don't allow anybody 
	to directly call us with an encoded link (helps to avoid possible hiding of phishing attempts)

2005-08-05  Jens Lautenbacher  <jtl@schlund.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/DerefServer.java: OK. Stop this insane stuff. Completely rewrote it.
	Now we base64 encode the link that comes in, and redirect via meta refresh to the derefserver again
	with this encoded information (in param enclink). This gets rid of the referer header. Then decode and use
	the location header with the original link without any checks (no JS will be evaled in http headers)

2005-08-05  Martin Leidig  <mleidig@schlund.de>
	
	Extended webservice error handling: via global and webservice specific
	faulthandlers SOAP faults can be customized or filtered (e.g. for logging,
	notification, information hiding). A custom faulthandler is written by
	deriving from the FaultHandler base class and overwriting the init() and
	handleFault(Fault) methods. The handler class has to be registered for a
	webservice or globally for all services by adding a <faulthandler class="..."/> 
	entry to the according section in the webservice configuration file.
	The handleFault() method will be automatically called after a
	webservice call ended up with an exception. The passed in Fault object
	contains the Throwable object and some context information, like the
	request URI and the Pustefix context. You can customize the fault by
	setting another Throwable object or SOAP faultstring, which then will
	be used for the further fault processing and which at last will be sent to
	the SOAP client (instead of the original ones).

	Modified:

	* example/common/conf/server-config.wsdd
	* example/core/build/create_webservice.xsl
	* example/webservice/conf/webservice.conf.in
	* skel/projects/common/conf/server-config.wsdd
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/Constants.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/WebServiceServlet.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/config/ConfigException.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/config/ConfigProperties.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/config/GlobalServiceConfig.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/config/ServiceConfig.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/generate/WebServiceTask.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/handler/AuthenticationHandler.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/handler/LoggingHandler.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/handler/MonitoringHandler.java

	Added:	

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/fault/EmailNotifyingHandler.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/fault/Fault.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/fault/FaultHandler.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/fault/InternalServerError.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/fault/LoggingHandler.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/handler/ErrorHandler.java

