2005-07-20  Jens Lautenbacher  <jtl@schlund.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/ServletManager.java: SECURITY: No longer use the plain session ID in a 
	cookie name (for the test of the secure cookie), but instead just the MD5. This way now there is no
	possibility to get to a valid secure session id without really reading the URL

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/generator/IWrapperParam.java (suppliedInRequest): new method,
	returns false when the whole parameter wasn't even supplied at all in the request (as opposed
	to just being supplied empty which would both result in the same null value)

