2005-05-30  Daniel Hopp <daniel.hopp@schlund.de>

	* pfx:elink window feature 'resizable' added

2005-05-30  Daniel Hopp <daniel.hopp@schlund.de>

	* made pfx:elink/@popupwidth and height optional in example/core/xsl/navigation.xsl.in

2005-05-30  Martin Leidig <mleidig@schlund.de>

	Added support for Axis 1.2 to Pustefix webservices. 
	
	WARNING: Due to incompatible changes in the WSDL types/XML Schema description
	generated from Java interfaces by Axis the message style RPC/literal does no
	longer work for Pustefix webservices in combination with Axis 1.1. You should
	switch to RPC/encoded by setting encoding/use in webservice.conf.in.

	* lib/wsif-2.0.jar: Removed. This library was used for WSDL types/XML schema
	processing during JS stub generation, as it doesn't support Axis 1.2, the schema
	handling now is done without help, low-level-style using the DOM directly.
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/generate/Wsdl2Js.java: Added DOM-style
	WSDL types/XML schema processing.

	Added the scope option to the global and webservice specific configuration.
	Up to now the default scope ("request") of Axis was always used, meaning that
	the webservice class was created on every request. Now you can additionally 
	set the scope to "session" (create once per session) or "application" (create
	once at all). 

	WARNING: The new default scope is "application", so check if you hold any 
	session or request specific state in your webservice class, if so change to
	the appropriate scope in webservice.conf.in.

	Added support for "scope" configuration option:
	* example/core/schema/wsconfig200401.xsd
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/config/ConfigProperties.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/config/GlobalServiceConfig.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/config/ServiceConfig.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/generate/WebServiceTask.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/Constants.java

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/generate/Wsdl2Java.java: API changes from
	Axis 1.1 to 1.2 now are handled via Reflection, so both APIs can be used without
	changes.
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/generate/Java2Wsdl.java: Use the default
	namespace also for interfaces (to keep interface and bean conventions unique).	
	* example/core/script/webservice.js: ArrayDeserializer no longer presupposes 
	any specific constraints on the name of value enumeration elements within 
	a SOAP encoded array (according to the SOAP 1.1 Encoding specification). 
	Removed creation of soapenc namespace declarations within literal style 
	serialization.
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/WebServiceServlet.java: Changed the
	development mode classloading mechanism (AppLoader usage), now Axis is forced 
	to use the custom classloader already on the servlet level by setting the current 
	thread's context classloader (at the start of request processing), it also has to 
	be set before starting the servlet initialization (before calling super.init()),
	as the AxisEngine already loads the classes while reading in the server
	deployment descriptor file. An AppLoader reload is simply done by 
	invalidating and reloading/reinitializing the AxisEngine (necessary because
 	the class cache isn't accessible/can't be cleared).
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/ResetClassLoaderHandler.java: Removed 
	Handler ClassLoader-setting/resetting
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/SetClassLoaderHandler.java: Also removed
	* ./example/common/conf/server-config.wsdd: Removed Axis-Handler for 
	Classloader-setting/resetting from request and response handler chain.
	* ./skel/projects/common/conf/server-config.wsdd: Also removed.	
	

2005-05-25  Daniel Hopp <daniel.hopp@schlund.de>

	* removed functions __js_getFormElement, __js_getFormElementWithValue from example/core/script/baselib.js

2005-05-24  Daniel Hopp <daniel.hopp@schlund.de>

