	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/Context.java: move calling of start ContextInterceptor down where
	all the stuff like vist_id that's read from the servlet request is already set.

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/ContextInterceptorFactory.java: need to use the apploader to 
	so all classes are loaded with the same classloader...

2005-04-21  Jens Lautenbacher  <jtl@schlund.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/ContextInterceptorFactory.java: new class, creates and stores ContextInterceptors 

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/ContextInterceptor.java (init): method removed, no need to init as no state is held.
	ContextInterceptors are singeltons!

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/Context.java: ContextInterceptors are now two chains of Interceptors, 
	one for start and one for end of request instead of two single instances. They are now created via a Factory, and
	are Singletons! For storing data use a ContextResource.
	* example/sample1/conf/config.prop.in: changed accordingly:
	<prop name="context.startinterceptor.001">de.schlund.pfixcore.example.SampleStartIC</prop>
	Interceptors now need a key to define the natural order.


	* example/core/build/create_propfiles.xsl: create index for
	ContextRessources with 3 instead of 2 digits (001 instead of 01)

