2005-04-18  Joerg Haecker <haecker@schlund.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/exceptionhandler/ExceptionContext.java:
	Added possibility to prevent request-parameter dump on error by 
	setting property 'servlet.paramdumponerror' to false in pustefix.prop.in.
	  
2005-04-18  Jens Lautenbacher  <jtl@schlund.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/targets/TargetGenerator.java: get page name and variant id from 
	attributes of the target node. 

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/SPDocument.java (getVariantFallbackArray): removed.
	(getVariant/setVariant): use the Variant type instead of Strings.
	(docIsUpdateable/setDocIsUpdateable): new methods

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/exceptionprocessor/util/ExceptionDataValueHelper.java: 
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/exceptionhandler/ExceptionContext.java: 
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/DirectOutputServlet.java: changed accordingly to changes in  PageRequest

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/AbstractXMLServer.java: handle variants, and put information about 
	used page variant into DOM tree 

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/PageRequestProperties.java: handle Variants and use Strings instead of 
	PageRequest objects (maybe this is not a good idea in this case after all, but it's OK for now)
	(getVariantMatchingPageRequestName) new method to return a page name with matching variantid.

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/PageRequest.java (createPageRequest):
	new static method to create a PageRequest while taking into account the currently valid variant.
	(isEmpty): removed. Now we use null to signal when no valid PageRequest is found.
	(getRootName): new method to return the name of the PageRequest without variantid attached.

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/PageMap.java: use page names, not PageRequest objects.

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/PageFlowManager.java: handle variants for flownames. 

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/PageFlow.java: only use page names internally, not pagerequests.
	getIndexOfPageRequest(PageRequest page) => getIndexOfPage(String page)
	containsPageRequest(PageRequest page)   => containsPage(String page) 
	etc.
	(getRootName) new method, to return the name of the pageflow without the variant attached.

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/FlowStep.java: Use page names
	as flow steps, not PageRequests (because of variants)

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/DirectOutputPageMap.java: Use
	page names, not pagerequests as keys. (because pagerequests also
	encode the variant id)

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/Context.java: Added start and
	end interceptors (See ContextInterceptor), which are called before
	and after the usual processing. These can be used to implement
	stuff that should be done regardless of the state that's called
	finally.  Use Variant as the type of variants.  All over the
	class, fix every creation of PageRequests or PageFlows to take
	into account the currently set variant.

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/Variant.java: added. Store variants in their own type. 

	* example/sample1/xml/two_frames.xml: 
	* example/sample1/xml/one_frame.xml: use CSS inline

	* example/sample1/txt/pages/main_home.xml: removed the whole layer
	stuff that's about to be removed anyway.  
	More cosmetics.

	* example/sample1/txt/styles.xml: cosmetics 

	* example/sample1/conf/depend.xml.in: remove css handling
	page. It's generating too much noise when testing.

	* example/sample1/conf/config.prop.in: demo new variant stuff 

	* example/core/xsl/master.xsl.in: remove the $variant
	parameter. You can get the used and requested variant ids from the DOM tree.

	* example/core/build/create_propfiles.xsl: implement variant
	handling for pagerequests and pageflows.  This is done by
	optionally allowing <default>..</default><variant
	name="..">..</variant>... as children for those tags.

	* example/core/build/create_depend.xsl: new attributes "page" and
	"variant" for targets. standardpage only has "variant". The
	associated page is now no longer determined by looking at a XSL
	param defined for a toplevel target, but only by using the page
	attribute (which will be used to set a XSL parameter, too,
	automatically)

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/ContextInterceptor.java: Added.
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/example/SampleStartIC.java: Sample
	ContextInterceptor that is used to set a variant id.

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/example/RandomVariantState.java: removed.

