2005-04-04  Martin Leidig  <mleidig@schlund.de>

	* example/core/build/create_depend.xsl: If no global or target specific outputencoding is specified,
	a node for the outputencoding stylesheet parameter with the project's encoding is inserted.
	* example/core/build/create_propfiles.xsl: Create 'servlet.encoding' from 'servletinfo/encoding'-node,
	which can be used to overwrite the servlet encoding's default (the project's encoding).
	* example/core/build/create_serverxml.xsl: Add URIEncoding attribute to the Connector elements. The value
	can be set in projects.xml.in. (/projects/common/tomcat/uriencoding).
	* example/core/build/create_webxml.xsl: Sets the project encoding as default servlet encoding by addding
	it as 'servlet.encoding' init parameter.
	* example/core/schema/properties200401.xsd: Added optional encoding element as servletinfo-child, which
	can be used to set the servlet's encoding resp. overwrite the project encoding.
	* example/sample1/conf/config.prop.in: Added encoding test page.
	* example/sample1/conf/depend.xml.in: Added encoding test page.
	* example/sample1/conf/project.xml.in: Added encoding element, defining the project's encoding (without
	an encoding element UTF-8 is taken as default).
	* example/servletconf/projects.xml.in: Added uriencoding element under /projects/common/tomcat (wihtout
	an encoding element UTF-8 is taken as default).
	* skel/build.xml: Added projects_xml target to dependcy list of targetdefs target.
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/ServletManager.java: Added method initServletEncoding() which gets the encoding
	from the servlet.encoding init parameter resp. the according property (overriding the init parameter).
	At the beginning of the doGet() method setCharacterEncoding() is called on the request and response
	objects to set the appropriate encoding.
	* example/sample1/txt/pages/main_encoding.xml: Added encoding test page.
	Added encoding test:
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/example/ContextEncodingTest.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/example/ContextEncodingTestImpl.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/example/EncodingTestHandler.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/example/EncodingTestState.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/example/iwrapper/EncodingTest.iwrp
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/util/URIParameters.java: Added helper class to get parameters from an URI
	urlencoded by an arbitrary encoding.


2005-04-01  Jens Lautenbacher  <jtl@schlund.de>

	* example/core/xsl/include.xsl.in: Implemented a fall back for lang nodes: If a lang node's @name ends with a '*',
	this node will work as a fallback for all languages starting with the @name (without the star). Example: you have
	<lang name="en_US">, <lang name="en_*">, <lang name="default">. If language is set to en_GB, the en_* node will be used, if it is
	set to en_US, the en_US lang node is used. In any other case the "default" lang node will be used (with other words,
	"default" still has its special meaning)

	add <pfx:langselect> template to have language switching also as an inline template (see also pfx:themeselect below)

2005-03-31  Jens Lautenbacher  <jtl@schlund.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/targets/VirtualTarget.java (generateValue): always supply a "themes" XSLT parameter containing
	all the valid themes for the target as a space separated list.

	* example/core/xsl/include.xsl.in: add <pfx:themeselect> to have the possibility to switch "inline", that means without
	having to create another include part, between different content based on the theme fallback queue.

2005-03-29  Jens Lautenbacher  <jtl@schlund.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/targets/VirtualTarget.java (setForceUpdate): new method, sets a boolean arg to true which
	will force an update of the target next time it's checked.
	(generateValue): set forceupdate back to false.

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/targets/AuxDependency.java (getModTime): getModTime again has no arguments.
	Now we call the new method setForceUpdate() on all the affected VirtualTargets
