2005-01-28  Martin Leidig  <mleidig@schlund.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/generate/WebServiceTask.java: Improved modification
	checking. Now also changes in any class depending on the interface are detected and will
	cause a regeneration of the according descriptors and stubs.
	* skel/build.xml: The 'pfx-webservice' task has a new attribute 'builddir', which has to
	be set for dependency checking to work.

2005-01-24  Jens Lautenbacher  <jtl@schlund.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/Context.java: Issue warning of level ERROR if
	pageflow is given, but not defined.

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/generator/IWrapper.java: add gimmeOrder to the interface
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/generator/IWrapperImpl.java: cat to IWrapper, not IWrapperImpl.

2005-01-20  Jens Lautenbacher  <jtl@schlund.de>

	* example/core/schema/properties200401.xsd: addedd boolean
	"logging" attribute to interface type

2005-01-17  Jens Lautenbacher  <jtl@schlund.de>

	* example/core/xsl/navigation.xsl.in: remove some unneeded
	instances where we automatically inserted target=_top into the
	generated links

2004-12-27  Daniel Hopp <daniel.hopp@schlund.de>

	* Minor changes to the templates pfx:image and pfx:xinp[@type='image'] in
	~/pfixcore/example/core/xsl/include.xsl.in and
	~/pfixcore/example/core/xsl/forminput.xsl.in:
	The 'alt'-attribute was added as xsl:param as well as an optional
	parameter called 'exclude-attributes', which contains a string of
	attribute names, _not_ to copy from context-node into the resulting
	img/input-element.
	'border="0"' removed from output-elements img/input[type=image], cause it's
	deprecated according to HTML 4.01 specification.

2004-12-21  Ute Platzer <up@schlund.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/app/DefaultAuthIWrapperState.java: in getDocument()
	method, use super.createDefaultResultDocument() instead of creating a new ResultDocument.

2004-12-21  Martin Leidig  <mleidig@schlund.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/multipart/TempFile.java: (Added) Temporary file implementation,
	which ensures that the associated physical file is deleted, when the object is no longer
	in use, i.e. when it gets finalized by the garbage collector.
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/multipart/FileData.java: Removed deletion, which now is done
	via the assigned TempFile instance.
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/multipart/MultipartHandler.java: Instead of java.io.File now
	the new TempFile class is used for representing file parts.

2004-12-20  Martin Leidig  <mleidig@schlund.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/multipart/FileData.java: Associated temporary files now are
	deleted when object gets finalized.
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/multipart/MultipartHandler.java: Temporary files exceeding the
	size limit now are deleted immediately.


2004-12-17  Jens Lautenbacher  <jtl@schlund.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/app/IWrapperSimpleContainer.java:
	implemented the "false" value for the pfx:command
	SUGGESTCONT. This will stop the IWrapperContainer from ever
	suggesting to advance in the pageflow. This is somewhat similar to
	the forcestop=true attribute, but it only works for
	DefaultIWrapperStates, while forcestop works regardless of the State. The difference
	bvetween the two is, that using SUGGESTCONT=false will still call retrieveCurrentStatus() on
	all Handlers in the group of Handlers selected by SELWRP (or all if there's no SELWRP used)
	and all Handlers that have alwaysretrieve set to "true" in the property file.

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/Context.java: starwithflow will
	now use the pageattribute to stop at that page in any case. That
	means, if the page is part of the pageflow that's checked, it will
	not be checked for needsData() past this page, but instead stopped
	there in any case. If the page is not part of the pageflow, it
	will be used instead of a possibly given final page.

2004-12-16  Niels Schelbach <niels@schlund.de>
        * example/core/build/iwrapper.xsl:
        * src/de/schlund/pfixcore/editor/handlers/EditUserDataHandler.java: Changed generation of
        iwrapper, so that paramnames are first letter uppercased for get set methods. Following
        common java bean convention.

2004-12-14  Adam Habermann  <adam.habermann@schlund.de>

	* skel/build.xml:
	"clean-project": do not fail if there is no dir.webapps
	"clean-jni": do not fail if there is no dir.jni

2004-12-13  Jens Lautenbacher  <jtl@schlund.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/Context.java: Changed the way a pageflow continuation is started. Now the default
	ist to always start a flow, unless context.prohibitContinue() has been called (from the State or a ContextRessource).
	removed some methods that are shouldn't be accessible from the outside anyway (getJumpToPage, getJumpToPageFlow).
	The PageMessage methods no longer have the error argument, such a situation can now be signalled via prohibitContinue().

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/ResultDocument.java: setContinue(), wantsContinue() REMOVED. ResultDocument is
	no longer used to signal the continuation of a pageflow, it's the default now that has to be explicitely prohibited
	by calling context.prohibitContinue() anywhere during a request cycle.

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/StateImpl.java (renderContextResources): new protected method.
	Descendants can call this to get the default handling (aka: inserting) of ContextResources.
	(addResponseHeadersAndType): new protected method. Can be used to get default handling of headers and mime type.
	(createDefaultResultDocument): uses both renderContextResources and addResponseHeadersAndType.
	This is the prime candidate for descendants to get a new ResultDocument.

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/app/StaticState.java:
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/app/DefaultIWrapperState.java:
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/app/DefaultAuthIWrapperState.java:
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/editor/handlers/SessionManagerState.java: Changed to use context.prohibitContinue()
	at the right places.

	* example/core/xsl/navigation.xsl.in:
	* example/core/xsl/forminput.xsl.in: <pfx:button>, <pfx:xinp
	  type="submit|image"> new attributes: @pageflow, @jumptopage,
	  @jumptopageflow, @forcestop. Also new pfx:commands: DESELWRP, SUGGESTCONT

2004-12-07  Adam Habermann  <adam.habermann@schlund.de>

	* xdocs/**: updated documentation
	* skel/build.xml:
	"check-permissions":
	finally changed to make all .sh files executable within dir.projects.
	"tomcat.dir.opt":
	make tomcat extract if there's no dir.tomcat/bin/catalina.sh instead of
	tomcat dir only; works around cvs empty dir bug on pristine checked out
	projects
	"clean-project":
	deletion of **/WEB-INF/web.xml

2004-12-07  Jens Lautenbacher  <jtl@schlund.de>

	* started 0.8.4-pre
	* released 0.8.3

	* example/core/build/create_depend.xsl: use global and local
	parameters now in all transformations for standardpage (not only
	the last one). Also no longer accept local definitions of product/lang in
	targets, always use the global from the make root node.

2004-12-06  Adam Habermann  <adam.habermann@schlund.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/util/XsltGenericTask.java
	Changed task, so the validate attribute may be true|false|dynamic.
	* skel/build.xml
	Added validation for target "propfiles". Changed property "validate" to
	dynamic validation to allow .prop.in files in old format to be transformed.
	* example/core/build/iwrapper.xsl
	Made it work with occurence and occurance.
	* src/**/*.iwrp
	replaced attribute name occurance by occurence.

2004-12-06  Jens Lautenbacher  <jtl@schlund.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/Context.java: added public addCookies method.
	added private storeCookies() to move the cookies into the SPDocument prior to returning.

2004-12-03  Adam Habermann  <adam.habermann@schlund.de>

	See following article for some background info about XML Schema
	within pustefix and the new format of the .prop.in files:
	http://sourceforge.net/mailarchive/forum.php?thread_id=5923414&forum_id=24420

	* example/core/schema/properties200401.xsd:
	XML Schema for .prop.in files
	* xdocs/prop.xml:
	new syntax for .prop.in files
	* xdocs/prop082.xml
	old syntax for .prop.in files
	* skel/build.xml:
	target "propfiles": turned on XML Schema validation
	* build.xml:
	target "testskel": added copy instruction for copying
	lib/tomcat/jakarta-tomcat-x.x.xx.tar.gz which is not included
	in pfixcore-skel-*.tar.gz anymore.
	* stuff/propconv200401:
	Tools for converting .prop.in files from syntax before XML Schema to
	new syntax.
	* example/core/prjtemplates/config.tmpl:
	converted to new format
	* **/prop.in:
	converted to new format
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/DirectOutputServer.java:
	made a subclass of DirectOutputServlet to come to a consistent naming
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/ServletManager.java:
	Changed processing of exception properties to:
	"exception" '.' JAVATYPE '.' ("forward"|"page"|"processor")
	This is to get rid of the <exception> tag within pustefix.prop.in,
	which did not comply to new format of <standardprops>.

2004-12-01  Joerg Haecker <haecker@schlund.de>

	* example/core/build/create_apacheconf.xsl: added match for literalauth-tag
	which can be used in project.xml for .htacces based auth.

2004-11-25  Jens Lautenbacher  <jtl@schlund.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/util/Cleanup.java: killed stupid Path bug (used without PathFactory!)

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/SPDocument.java: removed setCookies method
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/Context.java: added getRequestCookies method

2004-11-22  Jens Lautenbacher  <jtl@schlund.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/DerefServer.java: excape "<" and ">" for
	the displayed value of the link and urlencode the value used in
	the href. Thanks to Sebastian Marsching for the report. I hope
	this fixes the possible problem...

2004-11-22  Martin Leidig  <mleidig@schlund.de>

	Added client-side support of RPC/Literal encoding. Improved special
	character handling.

	* example/core/script/webservice.js: Encoding style and use now
	can be set at SOAP_Call objects via the setEncoding() method. The
	serialize() method of the serializer base class SOAP_SimpleSerializer
	and all derived classes now has an additional argument for passing
	a SOAP_SerializeCtx object, which represents the current serialization
	context and gives access to data needed during the serialization
	process (like the encoding use). Also improved special character
	handling: the XML_Writer method writeChars() now writes forbidden
	characters as entities.

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/generate/Wsdl2Js.java: Encoding
	style and use information now is read from the WSDL description and
	transformed into according SOAP_Call setEncoding() statements within
	the webservice stub methods.

2004-11-18  J???rg H???cker <haecker@schlund.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/util/email/EmailSender.java


2004-11-17  Jens Lautenbacher  <jtl@schlund.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/ServletManager.java: added the ability to
	specify in a new created session that it doesn't use cookies
	despite what the browser sends. This helps with situations where
	the test cookie is there, but the secure cookie has been
	denied. Fixed two code paths that seem to be affected by this.

2004-11-13  Jens Lautenbacher  <jtl@schlund.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/Context.java: fix javadoc

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/ServletManager.java: added the ability to specify with a property to NOT enforce a cookie check
	despite the session being marked already as using cookies. This is ONLY to cope with broken clients.

2004-11-11  Jens Lautenbacher  <jtl@schlund.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/app/DefaultIWrapperState.java:
	make sure that when the context returns true for
	pageMessageIsError() we add all the needed info to the resdoc

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/Context.java: Pagemessages now
	take another argument "iserror". If any pagemessage is supplied
	with this argument set to true, the Context will not enter the
	pageflow but will stay on the current page (much like it does in
	the case of an error).

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/example/ContextCounterImpl.java:
	* example/core/xsl/include.xsl.in:
	* example/core/txt/styles.xml: cosmetics, implement example

2004-11-09  Jens Lautenbacher  <jtl@schlund.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/Context.java: remove the __foreceauth reg param again. For now, we better
	try to re-auth just everytime we get a direct submit with __sendingauthdata set to 'true'.

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/ServletManager.java: more security stuff. Now we allow more than one secure
	session again by not only using one cookie, but instead naming the cookie according to the associated session
	(until now, the cookie was called __PFIX_SECURE_SESS__, now it's called __PFIX_SEC_<Session-Id>)

2004-11-08  Jens Lautenbacher  <jtl@schlund.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/Context.java: added __forceauth
	parameter to force a re-authentication.

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/handler/AuthenticationHandler.java:
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/DirectOutputServlet.java:
	change calls to checkAuthorization to supply "false" as forceauth argument.

2004-11-05  Jens Lautenbacher  <jtl@schlund.de>

	* started 0.8.3-pre

	* released 0.8.2

2004-11-04  Adam Habermann  <adam.habermann@schlund.de>

	* example/core/build/create_apacheconf.xsl:
	Implemented filtering out of duplicate Alias (<passthrough>) directives.

2004-10-31  Jens Lautenbacher  <jtl@schlund.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/ServletManager.java: final pieces in the security work: now we mark a session when it's used with a cookie
	enabled client and invalidate it whenever a later request doesn't supply cookies anymore.  This defeats clients who were
	able to get a foreign secure session id and try to work around the cookie based security features outlined below.

2004-10-29  Jens Lautenbacher  <jtl@schlund.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/ServletManager.java: bug fix: make it
	work without cookies again: we actually have to believe that the
	session is secure (if it is marked as such) when a request doesn't
	supply cookies at all.

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/PfixServletRequest.java: removed the pagemessage stuff...
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/Context.java: ...and moved it here completely.
	implemented the handling of args for pagemessages

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/ResultDocument.java (createIncludeFromStatusCode): made static as I need it
	from Context where I have no ResultDocument instance... a bit hackish. fixed all instances where it's used.

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/example/ContextCounterImpl.java: moved pagemessage setting to the CR, as it handles more
	cases of changing the counter value

	* example/common/dyntxt/statusmessages.xml: removed the "warning" attribute. It no longer makes sense.

	* example/core/txt/styles.xml:
	* example/core/script/baselib.js:
	* example/sample1/txt/pages/main_order.xml:
	* example/core/xsl/utils.xsl.in: remove progressbar stuff.

2004-10-28  Jens Lautenbacher  <jtl@schlund.de>

	* example/sample1/txt/pages/main_order.xml:
	* example/sample1/txt/pages/main_overview.xml: both pages can display warnings now

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/Context.java: consolidated the addPageMessage to
	have addPageMessage(Scode), addPageMessage(Scode, Level), addPageMessage(Scode, Level, Args[]).
	(insertPageMessages): Still more work to do to handle arguments at all....

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/PfixServletRequest.java: only one
	addPageMessage(Scode, Level, Args[]) method.

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/example/CounterHandler.java: changed accordingly

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/ServletManager.java: More security related work.
	The ServletManager will now prohibit the following cases:
	- A valid secure session is used but the request was not made under SSL
	- A valid secure session is used and the browser handles cookies but
	the __PFIX_SECURE_SSL_SESS__ cookie isn't found or it doesn't match the session id.

	Both cases will result in the secure session being invalidated.

2004-10-28  Benjamin Reitzammer  <benjamin@schlund.de>

	* Implemented the new pagemessages feature: Context has several new methods
	called addPageMessage(). With these you can associate a Statuscode with the
	next displayed page, no matter which page this is (this works with all
	pageflow/jumptopage stuff pustefix can do). Depending on the level, that's
	supplied with the StatusCode, the StatusCodes are wrapped in an according
	CSS class and a header is displayed too.
	To finally show the messages on a page, simply include use the <pfx:pagemessages />
	tag anywhere on your page, where you want messages to be shown.
	Take a look at the Context's Javadoc for details how to add StatusCodes
	to pages.

2004-10-27  Jens Lautenbacher  <jtl@schlund.de>

	* added xercesImpl-2.6.2 again. Seems it's still needed... :-(

