2004-06-22  Jens Lautenbacher  <jtl@schlund.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/Context.java (flowBeforeNeedsData):
	fixed an instance where it was possible that needsData() would be called on the handlers
	despite the fact that the whole page was inaccessible because of a prerequisitesMet() call
	returning true.

2004-06-22  Adam Habermann  <adam.habermann@schlund.de>

	* build.xml, skel/build.xml:
	target "compile": now passing ant property "javac.nowarn" to attribute
	nowarn of task javac.

2004-06-22  Joerg Haecker <haecker@schlund.de>

	* released 0.6.3, started 0.6.4-pre

2004-06-22  Benjamin Reitzammer <benjamin@schlund.de>

	* example/core/build/create_tomcatweb.xsl
	If you set project/includeexternalwebxml/@include to 'true' a web.xml that
	lies in the project's conf directory will be included into the final web.xml
	that's the result of the transformation. No checks regarding validity (beyond
	well-formedness) are performed on the included configuration.


2004-06-21  Joerg Haecker <haecker@schlund.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/AbstractXMLServer.java(handleDocument):
	Do not catch TargetGenerationExcpetions any more, they
	be processed by a defined ExceptionProcessor.
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/targets/TargetGenerationException.java: minor changes.
	* example/core/xsl/errorrepresentation.xsl.in: stylesheet for rendering errors on screen.
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/exceptionprocessor/UniversalExceptionProcessor.java:
	ExceptionProcessor rendering errors on screen.
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/ServletManager.java(callProcess):
	- if there is no processor defined for the passed throwable, use the old
	  exceptionhandler.
	- check if the passed throwable is an instance of the defined
	  throwable. If true, use the defined processor.
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/exceptionprocessor/ExceptionProcessor.java:
	added  parameter properties to the processException-method.
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/exceptionprocessor/PageForwardingExceptionProcessor.java:
	adjusted to above changes.
	* example/common/conf/pustefix.prop.in: added
	UniversalExceptionProcessor for all Throwables in test-mode.
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/exceptionprocessor/ExceptionDataValueHelper.java:
	added new helper class.
	* lib/rmiobj.jar: added jar with value-objects and helper classes.

